47 // Macro for outputting trace information from representation inference.
48 #define TRACE(...) \
49  do { \
50  if (v8_flags.trace_representation) PrintF(__VA_ARGS__); \
51  } while (false)
52 
53 const char* kSimplifiedLoweringReducerName = "SimplifiedLowering";
54 
55 // Representation selection and lowering of {Simplified} operators to machine
56 // operators are interwined. We use a fixpoint calculation to compute both the
57 // output representation and the best possible lowering for {Simplified} nodes.
58 // Representation change insertion ensures that all values are in the correct
59 // machine representation after this phase, as dictated by the machine
60 // operators themselves.
61 enum Phase {
62  // 1.) PROPAGATE: Traverse the graph from the end, pushing usage information
63  // backwards from uses to definitions, around cycles in phis, according
64  // to local rules for each operator.
65  // During this phase, the usage information for a node determines the best
66  // possible lowering for each operator so far, and that in turn determines
67  // the output representation.
68  // Therefore, to be correct, this phase must iterate to a fixpoint before
69  // the next phase can begin.
70  PROPAGATE,
71 
72  // 2.) RETYPE: Propagate types from type feedback forwards.
73  RETYPE,
74 
75  // 3.) LOWER: perform lowering for all {Simplified} nodes by replacing some
76  // operators for some nodes, expanding some nodes to multiple nodes, or
77  // removing some (redundant) nodes.
78  // During this phase, use the {RepresentationChanger} to insert
79  // representation changes between uses that demand a particular
80  // representation and nodes that produce a different representation.
81  LOWER
82 };
83

86 MachineRepresentation MachineRepresentationFromArrayType(
87  ExternalArrayType array_type) {
88  switch (array_type) {
89  case kExternalUint8Array:
90  case kExternalUint8ClampedArray:
91  case kExternalInt8Array:
92  return MachineRepresentation::kWord8;
93  case kExternalUint16Array:
94  case kExternalInt16Array:
95  return MachineRepresentation::kWord16;
96  case kExternalUint32Array:
97  case kExternalInt32Array:
98  return MachineRepresentation::kWord32;
99  case kExternalFloat16Array:
100  return MachineRepresentation::kFloat16RawBits;
101  case kExternalFloat32Array:
102  return MachineRepresentation::kFloat32;
103  case kExternalFloat64Array:
104  return MachineRepresentation::kFloat64;
105  case kExternalBigInt64Array:
106  case kExternalBigUint64Array:
107  return MachineRepresentation::kWord64;
108  }
109  UNREACHABLE();
110 }
111 
112 UseInfo CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(
113  NumberOperationHint hint, IdentifyZeros identify_zeros = kDistinguishZeros,
114  const FeedbackSource& feedback = FeedbackSource()) {
115  switch (hint) {
116  case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
117  case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs:
118  return UseInfo::CheckedSignedSmallAsWord32(identify_zeros, feedback);
119  case NumberOperationHint::kAdditiveSafeInteger:
120  case NumberOperationHint::kNumber:
121  DCHECK_EQ(identify_zeros, kIdentifyZeros);
122  return UseInfo::CheckedNumberAsWord32(feedback);
123  case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrBoolean:
124  // Not used currently.
125  UNREACHABLE();
126  case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball:
127  DCHECK_EQ(identify_zeros, kIdentifyZeros);
128  return UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsWord32(feedback);
129  }
130  UNREACHABLE();
131 }
132 
133 UseInfo CheckedUseInfoAsFloat64FromHint(
134  NumberOperationHint hint, const FeedbackSource& feedback,
135  IdentifyZeros identify_zeros = kDistinguishZeros) {
136  switch (hint) {
137  case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
138  case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs:
139  // Not used currently.
140  UNREACHABLE();
141  case NumberOperationHint::kAdditiveSafeInteger:
142  case NumberOperationHint::kNumber:
143  return UseInfo::CheckedNumberAsFloat64(identify_zeros, feedback);
144  case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrBoolean:
145  return UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrBooleanAsFloat64(identify_zeros, feedback);
146  case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball:
147  return UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(identify_zeros, feedback);
148  }
149  UNREACHABLE();
150 }
151 
152 UseInfo TruncatingUseInfoFromRepresentation(
153  MachineRepresentation rep, const Type& type_hint = Type::Any()) {
154  switch (rep) {
155  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned:
156  return UseInfo::TaggedSigned();
157  case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer:
158  case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
159  case MachineRepresentation::kIndirectPointer:
160  case MachineRepresentation::kMapWord:
161  return UseInfo::AnyTagged();
162  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
163 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
164  if (type_hint.Maybe(Type::Undefined())) {
165  return UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64OrUndefined();
166  }
167 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
168  return UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64();
169  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
170  return UseInfo::Float32();
171  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16RawBits:
172  return UseInfo::Float16RawBits();
173  case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
174  case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
175  case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
176  return UseInfo::TruncatingWord32();
177  case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
178  return UseInfo::TruncatingWord64();
179  case MachineRepresentation::kBit:
180  return UseInfo::Bool();
181  case MachineRepresentation::kCompressedPointer:
182  case MachineRepresentation::kCompressed:
183  case MachineRepresentation::kProtectedPointer:
184  case MachineRepresentation::kSandboxedPointer:
185  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
186  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
187  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256:
188  case MachineRepresentation::kNone:
189  UNREACHABLE();
190  }
191 }

193 UseInfo UseInfoForBasePointer(const FieldAccess& access) {
194  return access.tag() != 0 ? UseInfo::AnyTagged() : UseInfo::Word();
195 }

197 UseInfo UseInfoForBasePointer(const ElementAccess& access) {
198  return access.tag() != 0 ? UseInfo::AnyTagged() : UseInfo::Word();

201 void ReplaceEffectControlUses(Node* node, Node* effect, Node* control) {
202  for (Edge edge : node->use_edges()) {
203  if (NodeProperties::IsControlEdge(edge)) {
204  edge.UpdateTo(control);
205  } else if (NodeProperties::IsEffectEdge(edge)) {
206  edge.UpdateTo(effect);
207  } else {
208  DCHECK(NodeProperties::IsValueEdge(edge) ||
209  NodeProperties::IsContextEdge(edge));
210  }
211  }
212 }
213 
214 bool CanOverflowSigned32(const Operator* op, Type left, Type right,
215  TypeCache const* type_cache, Zone* type_zone) {
216  // We assume the inputs are checked Signed32 (or known statically to be
217  // Signed32). Technically, the inputs could also be minus zero, which we treat
218  // as 0 for the purpose of this function.
219  if (left.Maybe(Type::MinusZero())) {
220  left = Type::Union(left, type_cache->kSingletonZero, type_zone);
221  }
222  if (right.Maybe(Type::MinusZero())) {
223  right = Type::Union(right, type_cache->kSingletonZero, type_zone);
224  }
225  left = Type::Intersect(left, Type::Signed32(), type_zone);
226  right = Type::Intersect(right, Type::Signed32(), type_zone);
227  if (left.IsNone() || right.IsNone()) return false;
228  switch (op->opcode()) {
229  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeSmallIntegerAdd:
230  return (left.Max() + right.Max() > kMaxInt) ||
231  (left.Min() + right.Min() < kMinInt);
232 
233  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeSmallIntegerSubtract:
234  return (left.Max() - right.Min() > kMaxInt) ||
235  (left.Min() - right.Max() < kMinInt);
236 
237  default:
238  UNREACHABLE();
239  }
240 }
241 
242 bool IsSomePositiveOrderedNumber(Type type) {
243  return type.Is(Type::OrderedNumber()) && (type.IsNone() || type.Min() > 0);
244 }
245 
246 inline bool IsLargeBigInt(Type type) {
247  return type.Is(Type::BigInt()) && !type.Is(Type::SignedBigInt64()) &&
248  !type.Is(Type::UnsignedBigInt64());
249 }

268 bool IsLoadFloat16ArrayElement(Node* node) {
269  Operator::Opcode opcode = node->op()->opcode();
270  return (opcode == IrOpcode::kLoadTypedElement ||
271  opcode == IrOpcode::kLoadDataViewElement) &&
272  ExternalArrayTypeOf(node->op()) == kExternalFloat16Array;
273 }

277 #ifdef DEBUG
278 // Helpers for monotonicity checking.
279 class InputUseInfos {
280  public:
281  explicit InputUseInfos(Zone* zone) : input_use_infos_(zone) {}
282 
283  void SetAndCheckInput(Node* node, int index, UseInfo use_info) {
284  if (input_use_infos_.empty()) {
285  input_use_infos_.resize(node->InputCount(), UseInfo::None());
286  }
287  // Check that the new use informatin is a super-type of the old
288  // one.
289  DCHECK(IsUseLessGeneral(input_use_infos_[index], use_info));
290  input_use_infos_[index] = use_info;
291  }
292 
293  private:
294  ZoneVector<UseInfo> input_use_infos_;
295 
296  static bool IsUseLessGeneral(UseInfo use1, UseInfo use2) {
297  return use1.truncation().IsLessGeneralThan(use2.truncation());
298  }
299 };

303 class RepresentationSelector {
304  // The purpose of this nested class is to hide method
305  // v8::internal::compiler::NodeProperties::ChangeOp which should not be
306  // directly used by code in RepresentationSelector and SimplifiedLowering.
307  // RepresentationSelector code should call RepresentationSelector::ChangeOp in
308  // place of NodeProperties::ChangeOp, in order to notify the changes to a
309  // registered ObserveNodeManager and support the %ObserveNode intrinsic.
310  class NodeProperties : public compiler::NodeProperties {
311  static void ChangeOp(Node* node, const Operator* new_op) { UNREACHABLE(); }
312  };
313 
314  public:
315  // Information for each node tracked during the fixpoint.
316  class NodeInfo final {
317  public:
318  // Adds new use to the node. Returns true if something has changed
319  // and the node has to be requeued.
320  bool AddUse(UseInfo info) {
321  Truncation old_truncation = truncation_;
322  truncation_ = Truncation::Generalize(truncation_, info.truncation());
323  return truncation_ != old_truncation;
324  }
325 
326  void set_queued() { state_ = kQueued; }
327  void set_visited() { state_ = kVisited; }
328  void set_pushed() { state_ = kPushed; }
329  void reset_state() { state_ = kUnvisited; }
330  bool visited() const { return state_ == kVisited; }
331  bool queued() const { return state_ == kQueued; }
332  bool pushed() const { return state_ == kPushed; }
333  bool unvisited() const { return state_ == kUnvisited; }
334  Truncation truncation() const { return truncation_; }
335  void set_output(MachineRepresentation output) { representation_ = output; }
336 
337  MachineRepresentation representation() const { return representation_; }
338 
339  // Helpers for feedback typing.
340  void set_feedback_type(Type type) { feedback_type_ = type; }
341  Type feedback_type() const { return feedback_type_; }
342  void set_weakened() { weakened_ = true; }
343  bool weakened() const { return weakened_; }
344  void set_restriction_type(Type type) { restriction_type_ = type; }
345  Type restriction_type() const { return restriction_type_; }
346 
347  private:
348  // Fields are ordered to avoid mixing byte and word size fields to minimize
349  // padding.
350  enum State : uint8_t { kUnvisited, kPushed, kVisited, kQueued };
351  State state_ = kUnvisited;
352  MachineRepresentation representation_ =
353  MachineRepresentation::kNone; // Output representation.
354  Truncation truncation_ = Truncation::None(); // Information about uses.
355  bool weakened_ = false;
356 
357  Type restriction_type_ = Type::Any();
358  Type feedback_type_;
359  };

361  RepresentationSelector(JSGraph* jsgraph, JSHeapBroker* broker, Zone* zone,
362  RepresentationChanger* changer,
363  SourcePositionTable* source_positions,
364  NodeOriginTable* node_origins,
365  TickCounter* tick_counter, Linkage* linkage,
366  ObserveNodeManager* observe_node_manager,
367  SimplifiedLoweringVerifier* verifier)
368  : jsgraph_(jsgraph),
369  broker_(broker),
370  zone_(zone),
371  might_need_revisit_(zone),
372  count_(jsgraph->graph()->NodeCount()),
373  info_(count_, zone),
374 #ifdef DEBUG
375  node_input_use_infos_(count_, InputUseInfos(zone), zone),
376 #endif
377  replacements_(zone),
378  changer_(changer),
379  revisit_queue_(zone),
380  traversal_nodes_(zone),
381  source_positions_(source_positions),
382  node_origins_(node_origins),
383  type_cache_(TypeCache::Get()),
384  op_typer_(broker, graph_zone()),
385  tick_counter_(tick_counter),
386  linkage_(linkage),
387  observe_node_manager_(observe_node_manager),
388  verifier_(verifier) {
389  singleton_true_ =
390  Type::Constant(broker, broker->true_value(), graph_zone());
391  singleton_false_ =
392  Type::Constant(broker, broker->false_value(), graph_zone());
393  }

395  bool verification_enabled() const { return verifier_ != nullptr; }
396 
397  void ResetNodeInfoState() {
398  // Clean up for the next phase.
399  for (NodeInfo& info : info_) {
400  info.reset_state();
401  }
402  }
403 
404  Type TypeOf(Node* node) {
405  Type type = GetInfo(node)->feedback_type();
406  return type.IsInvalid() ? NodeProperties::GetType(node) : type;
407  }
408 
409  Type FeedbackTypeOf(Node* node) {
410  Type type = GetInfo(node)->feedback_type();
411  return type.IsInvalid() ? Type::None() : type;
412  }
413 
414  Type TypePhi(Node* node) {
415  int arity = node->op()->ValueInputCount();
416  Type type = FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
417  for (int i = 1; i < arity; ++i) {
418  type = op_typer_.Merge(type, FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(i)));
419  }
420  return type;
421  }
422 
423  Type TypeSelect(Node* node) {
424  return op_typer_.Merge(FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(1)),
425  FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(2)));
426  }
427 
428  bool UpdateFeedbackType(Node* node) {
429  if (node->op()->ValueOutputCount() == 0) return false;
430  if ((IrOpcode::IsMachineOpcode(node->opcode()) ||
431  IrOpcode::IsMachineConstantOpcode(node->opcode())) &&
432  node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kLoadFramePointer) {
433  DCHECK(NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Machine()));
434  }
435 
436  // For any non-phi node just wait until we get all inputs typed. We only
437  // allow untyped inputs for phi nodes because phis are the only places
438  // where cycles need to be broken.
439  if (node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kPhi) {
440  for (int i = 0; i < node->op()->ValueInputCount(); i++) {
441  if (GetInfo(node->InputAt(i))->feedback_type().IsInvalid()) {
442  return false;
443  }
444  }
445  }
446 
447  NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
448  Type type = info->feedback_type();
449  Type new_type = NodeProperties::GetType(node);
450 
451  // We preload these values here to avoid increasing the binary size too
452  // much, which happens if we inline the calls into the macros below.
453  Type input0_type;
454  if (node->InputCount() > 0) input0_type = FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
455  Type input1_type;
456  if (node->InputCount() > 1) input1_type = FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
457 
458  switch (node->opcode()) {
459 #define DECLARE_CASE(Name) \
460  case IrOpcode::k##Name: { \
461  new_type = op_typer_.Name(input0_type, input1_type); \
462  break; \
463  }
464  SIMPLIFIED_NUMBER_BINOP_LIST(DECLARE_CASE)
465  DECLARE_CASE(SameValue)
466 #undef DECLARE_CASE
467 
468 #define DECLARE_CASE(Name) \
469  case IrOpcode::k##Name: { \
470  new_type = Type::Intersect(op_typer_.Name(input0_type, input1_type), \
471  info->restriction_type(), graph_zone()); \
472  break; \
473  }
474  SIMPLIFIED_SPECULATIVE_NUMBER_BINOP_LIST(DECLARE_CASE)
475  SIMPLIFIED_SPECULATIVE_BIGINT_BINOP_LIST(DECLARE_CASE)
476 #undef DECLARE_CASE
477 
478 #define DECLARE_CASE(Name) \
479  case IrOpcode::k##Name: { \
480  new_type = op_typer_.Name(input0_type); \
481  break; \
482  }
483  SIMPLIFIED_NUMBER_UNOP_LIST(DECLARE_CASE)
484 #undef DECLARE_CASE
485 
486 #define DECLARE_CASE(Name) \
487  case IrOpcode::k##Name: { \
488  new_type = Type::Intersect(op_typer_.Name(input0_type), \
489  info->restriction_type(), graph_zone()); \
490  break; \
491  }
492  SIMPLIFIED_SPECULATIVE_NUMBER_UNOP_LIST(DECLARE_CASE)
493 #undef DECLARE_CASE
494 
495  case IrOpcode::kConvertReceiver:
496  new_type = op_typer_.ConvertReceiver(input0_type);
497  break;
498 
499  case IrOpcode::kPlainPrimitiveToNumber:
500  new_type = op_typer_.ToNumber(input0_type);
501  break;
502 
503  case IrOpcode::kCheckBounds:
504  new_type =
505  Type::Intersect(op_typer_.CheckBounds(input0_type, input1_type),
506  info->restriction_type(), graph_zone());
507  break;
508 
509  case IrOpcode::kCheckFloat64Hole:
510  new_type = Type::Intersect(op_typer_.CheckFloat64Hole(input0_type),
511  info->restriction_type(), graph_zone());
512  break;
513 
514  case IrOpcode::kCheckNumber:
515  new_type = Type::Intersect(op_typer_.CheckNumber(input0_type),
516  info->restriction_type(), graph_zone());
517  break;
518 
519  case IrOpcode::kCheckNumberOrUndefined:
520  new_type =
521  Type::Intersect(op_typer_.CheckNumberOrUndefined(input0_type),
522  info->restriction_type(), graph_zone());
523  break;
524 
525  case IrOpcode::kCheckNumberFitsInt32:
526  new_type = Type::Intersect(op_typer_.CheckNumberFitsInt32(input0_type),
527  info->restriction_type(), graph_zone());
528  break;
529 
530  case IrOpcode::kPhi: {
531  new_type = TypePhi(node);
532  if (!type.IsInvalid()) {
533  new_type = Weaken(node, type, new_type);
534  }
535  break;
536  }
537 
538  case IrOpcode::kConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined:
539  new_type = op_typer_.ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(
540  FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(0)));
541  break;
542 
543  case IrOpcode::kTypeGuard: {
544  new_type = op_typer_.TypeTypeGuard(node->op(),
545  FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(0)));
546  break;
547  }
548 
549  case IrOpcode::kSelect: {
550  const auto& p = SelectParametersOf(node->op());
551  if (p.semantics() == BranchSemantics::kMachine) {
552  if (type.IsInvalid()) {
553  GetInfo(node)->set_feedback_type(NodeProperties::GetType(node));
554  return true;
555  }
556  return false;
557  }
558  new_type = TypeSelect(node);
559  break;
560  }
561 
562  default:
563  // Shortcut for operations that we do not handle.
564  if (type.IsInvalid()) {
565  GetInfo(node)->set_feedback_type(NodeProperties::GetType(node));
566  return true;
567  }
568  return false;
569  }
570  // We need to guarantee that the feedback type is a subtype of the upper
571  // bound. Naively that should hold, but weakening can actually produce
572  // a bigger type if we are unlucky with ordering of phi typing. To be
573  // really sure, just intersect the upper bound with the feedback type.
574  new_type = Type::Intersect(GetUpperBound(node), new_type, graph_zone());
575 
576  if (!type.IsInvalid() && new_type.Is(type)) return false;
577  GetInfo(node)->set_feedback_type(new_type);
578  if (v8_flags.trace_representation) {
579  PrintNodeFeedbackType(node);
580  }
581  return true;
582  }
583 
584  void PrintNodeFeedbackType(Node* n) {
585  StdoutStream os;
586  os << "#" << n->id() << ":" << *n->op() << "(";
587  int j = 0;
588  for (Node* const i : n->inputs()) {
589  if (j++ > 0) os << ", ";
590  os << "#" << i->id() << ":" << i->op()->mnemonic();
591  }
592  os << ")";
593  if (NodeProperties::IsTyped(n)) {
594  Type static_type = NodeProperties::GetType(n);
595  os << " [Static type: " << static_type;
596  Type feedback_type = GetInfo(n)->feedback_type();
597  if (!feedback_type.IsInvalid() && feedback_type != static_type) {
598  os << ", Feedback type: " << feedback_type;
599  }
600  os << "]";
601  }
602  os << std::endl;
603  }
604 
605  Type Weaken(Node* node, Type previous_type, Type current_type) {
606  // If the types have nothing to do with integers, return the types.
607  Type const integer = type_cache_->kInteger;
608  if (!previous_type.Maybe(integer)) {
609  return current_type;
610  }
611  DCHECK(current_type.Maybe(integer));
612 
613  Type current_integer = Type::Intersect(current_type, integer, graph_zone());
614  DCHECK(!current_integer.IsNone());
615  Type previous_integer =
616  Type::Intersect(previous_type, integer, graph_zone());
617  DCHECK(!previous_integer.IsNone());
618 
619  // Once we start weakening a node, we should always weaken.
620  if (!GetInfo(node)->weakened()) {
621  // Only weaken if there is range involved; we should converge quickly
622  // for all other types (the exception is a union of many constants,
623  // but we currently do not increase the number of constants in unions).
624  Type previous = previous_integer.GetRange();
625  Type current = current_integer.GetRange();
626  if (current.IsInvalid() || previous.IsInvalid()) {
627  return current_type;
628  }
629  // Range is involved => we are weakening.
630  GetInfo(node)->set_weakened();
631  }
632 
633  return Type::Union(current_type,
634  op_typer_.WeakenRange(previous_integer, current_integer),
635  graph_zone());
636  }
637 
638  // Generates a pre-order traversal of the nodes, starting with End.
639  void GenerateTraversal() {
640  // Reset previous state.
641  ResetNodeInfoState();
642  traversal_nodes_.clear();
643  count_ = graph()->NodeCount();
644  info_.resize(count_);
645 
646  ZoneStack<NodeState> stack(zone_);
647 
648  stack.push({graph()->end(), 0});
649  GetInfo(graph()->end())->set_pushed();
650  while (!stack.empty()) {
651  NodeState& current = stack.top();
652  Node* node = current.node;
653  // If there is an unvisited input, push it and continue with that node.
654  bool pushed_unvisited = false;
655  while (current.input_index < node->InputCount()) {
656  Node* input = node->InputAt(current.input_index);
657  NodeInfo* input_info = GetInfo(input);
658  current.input_index++;
659  if (input_info->unvisited()) {
660  input_info->set_pushed();
661  stack.push({input, 0});
662  pushed_unvisited = true;
663  break;
664  } else if (input_info->pushed()) {
665  // Optimization for the Retype phase.
666  // If we had already pushed (and not visited) an input, it means that
667  // the current node will be visited in the Retype phase before one of
668  // its inputs. If this happens, the current node might need to be
669  // revisited.
670  MarkAsPossibleRevisit(node, input);
671  }
672  }
673 
674  if (pushed_unvisited) continue;
675 
676  stack.pop();
677  NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
678  info->set_visited();
679 
680  // Generate the traversal
681  traversal_nodes_.push_back(node);
682  }
683  }
684 
685  void PushNodeToRevisitIfVisited(Node* node) {
686  NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
687  if (info->visited()) {
688  TRACE(" QUEUEING #%d: %s\n", node->id(), node->op()->mnemonic());
689  info->set_queued();
690  revisit_queue_.push(node);
691  }
692  }
693 
694  // Tries to update the feedback type of the node, as well as setting its
695  // machine representation (in VisitNode). Returns true iff updating the
696  // feedback type is successful.
697  bool RetypeNode(Node* node) {
698  NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
699  info->set_visited();
700  bool updated = UpdateFeedbackType(node);
701  TRACE(" visit #%d: %s\n", node->id(), node->op()->mnemonic());
702  VisitNode<RETYPE>(node, info->truncation(), nullptr);
703  TRACE(" ==> output %s\n", MachineReprToString(info->representation()));
704  return updated;
705  }
706 
707  // Visits the node and marks it as visited. Inside of VisitNode, we might
708  // change the truncation of one of our inputs (see EnqueueInput<PROPAGATE> for
709  // this). If we change the truncation of an already visited node, we will add
710  // it to the revisit queue.
711  void PropagateTruncation(Node* node) {
712  NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
713  info->set_visited();
714  TRACE(" visit #%d: %s (trunc: %s)\n", node->id(), node->op()->mnemonic(),
715  info->truncation().description());
716  VisitNode<PROPAGATE>(node, info->truncation(), nullptr);
717  }
718 
719  // Backward propagation of truncations to a fixpoint.
720  void RunPropagatePhase() {
721  TRACE("--{Propagate phase}--\n");
722  ResetNodeInfoState();
723  DCHECK(revisit_queue_.empty());
724 
725  // Process nodes in reverse post order, with End as the root.
726  for (auto it = traversal_nodes_.crbegin(); it != traversal_nodes_.crend();
727  ++it) {
728  PropagateTruncation(*it);
729 
730  while (!revisit_queue_.empty()) {
731  Node* node = revisit_queue_.front();
732  revisit_queue_.pop();
733  PropagateTruncation(node);
734  }
735  }
736  }
737 
738  // Forward propagation of types from type feedback to a fixpoint.
739  void RunRetypePhase() {
740  TRACE("--{Retype phase}--\n");
741  ResetNodeInfoState();
742  DCHECK(revisit_queue_.empty());
743 
744  for (auto it = traversal_nodes_.cbegin(); it != traversal_nodes_.cend();
745  ++it) {
746  Node* node = *it;
747  if (!RetypeNode(node)) continue;
748 
749  auto revisit_it = might_need_revisit_.find(node);
750  if (revisit_it == might_need_revisit_.end()) continue;
751 
752  for (Node* const user : revisit_it->second) {
753  PushNodeToRevisitIfVisited(user);
754  }
755 
756  // Process the revisit queue.
757  while (!revisit_queue_.empty()) {
758  Node* revisit_node = revisit_queue_.front();
759  revisit_queue_.pop();
760  if (!RetypeNode(revisit_node)) continue;
761  // Here we need to check all uses since we can't easily know which
762  // nodes will need to be revisited due to having an input which was
763  // a revisited node.
764  for (Node* const user : revisit_node->uses()) {
765  PushNodeToRevisitIfVisited(user);
766  }
767  }
768  }
769  }
770 
771  // Lowering and change insertion phase.
772  void RunLowerPhase(SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
773  TRACE("--{Lower phase}--\n");
774  for (auto it = traversal_nodes_.cbegin(); it != traversal_nodes_.cend();
775  ++it) {
776  Node* node = *it;
777  NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
778  TRACE(" visit #%d: %s\n", node->id(), node->op()->mnemonic());
779  // Reuse {VisitNode()} so the representation rules are in one place.
780  SourcePositionTable::Scope scope(
781  source_positions_, source_positions_->GetSourcePosition(node));
782  NodeOriginTable::Scope origin_scope(node_origins_, "simplified lowering",
783  node);
784  VisitNode<LOWER>(node, info->truncation(), lowering);
785  }
786 
787  // Perform the final replacements.
788  for (NodeVector::iterator i = replacements_.begin();
789  i != replacements_.end(); ++i) {
790  Node* node = *i;
791  Node* replacement = *(++i);
792  node->ReplaceUses(replacement);
793  node->Kill();
794  // We also need to replace the node in the rest of the vector.
795  for (NodeVector::iterator j = i + 1; j != replacements_.end(); ++j) {
796  ++j;
797  if (*j == node) *j = replacement;
798  }
799  }
800  }
801 
802  void RunVerifyPhase(OptimizedCompilationInfo* compilation_info) {
803  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(verifier_);
804 
805  TRACE("--{Verify Phase}--\n");
806 
807  // Patch pending type overrides.
808  for (const auto& [constant, uses] :
809  verifier_->machine_uses_of_constants()) {
810  Node* typed_constant =
811  InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(Type::Machine(), constant);
812  for (auto use : uses) {
813  for (int i = 0; i < use->InputCount(); ++i) {
814  if (use->InputAt(i) == constant) {
815  use->ReplaceInput(i, typed_constant);
816  }
817  }
818  }
819  }
820 
821  // Generate a new traversal containing all the new nodes created during
822  // lowering.
823  GenerateTraversal();
824 
825  // Set node types to the refined types computed during retyping.
826  for (Node* node : traversal_nodes_) {
827  NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
828  if (!info->feedback_type().IsInvalid()) {
829  NodeProperties::SetType(node, info->feedback_type());
830  }
831  }
832 
833  // Print graph.
834  if (compilation_info != nullptr && compilation_info->trace_turbo_json()) {
835  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded scope(broker_);
836  AllowHandleDereference allow_deref;
837 
838  TurboJsonFile json_of(compilation_info, std::ios_base::app);
839  JSONGraphWriter writer(json_of, graph(), source_positions_,
840  node_origins_);
841  writer.PrintPhase("V8.TFSimplifiedLowering [after lower]");
842  }
843 
844  // Verify all nodes.
845  for (Node* node : traversal_nodes_) {
846  verifier_->VisitNode(node, op_typer_);
847  }
848 
849  // Print graph.
850  if (compilation_info != nullptr && compilation_info->trace_turbo_json()) {
851  UnparkedScopeIfNeeded scope(broker_);
852  AllowHandleDereference allow_deref;
853 
854  TurboJsonFile json_of(compilation_info, std::ios_base::app);
855  JSONGraphWriterWithVerifierTypes writer(
856  json_of, graph(), source_positions_, node_origins_, verifier_);
857  writer.PrintPhase("V8.TFSimplifiedLowering [after verify]");
858  }
859 
860  // Eliminate all introduced hints.
861  for (Node* node : verifier_->inserted_hints()) {
862  Node* input = node->InputAt(0);
863  node->ReplaceUses(input);
864  node->Kill();
865  }
866  }
867 
868  void Run(SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
869  GenerateTraversal();
870  RunPropagatePhase();
871  RunRetypePhase();
872  RunLowerPhase(lowering);
873  if (verification_enabled()) {
874  RunVerifyPhase(lowering->info_);
875  }
876  }
877 
878  // Just assert for Retype and Lower. Propagate specialized below.
879  template <Phase T>
880  void EnqueueInput(Node* use_node, int index,
881  UseInfo use_info = UseInfo::None()) {
882  static_assert(retype<T>() || lower<T>(),
883  "This version of EnqueueInput has to be called in "
884  "the Retype or Lower phase.");
885  }
886 
887  template <Phase T>
888  static constexpr bool propagate() {
889  return T == PROPAGATE;
890  }
891 
892  template <Phase T>
893  static constexpr bool retype() {
894  return T == RETYPE;
895  }
896 
897  template <Phase T>
898  static constexpr bool lower() {
899  return T == LOWER;
900  }
901 
902  template <Phase T>
903  void SetOutput(Node* node, MachineRepresentation representation,
904  Type restriction_type = Type::Any());
905 
906  Type GetUpperBound(Node* node) { return NodeProperties::GetType(node); }
907 
908  bool InputCannotBe(Node* node, Type type) {
909  DCHECK_EQ(1, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
910  return !GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0)).Maybe(type);
911  }
912 
913  bool InputIs(Node* node, Type type) {
914  DCHECK_EQ(1, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
915  return GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0)).Is(type);
916  }
917 
918  bool BothInputsAreSigned32(Node* node) {
919  return BothInputsAre(node, Type::Signed32());
920  }
921 
922  bool BothInputsAreUnsigned32(Node* node) {
923  return BothInputsAre(node, Type::Unsigned32());
924  }
925 
926  bool BothInputsAre(Node* node, Type type) {
927  DCHECK_EQ(2, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
928  return GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0)).Is(type) &&
929  GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1)).Is(type);
930  }
931 
932  bool IsNodeRepresentationTagged(Node* node) {
933  MachineRepresentation representation = GetInfo(node)->representation();
934  return IsAnyTagged(representation);
935  }
936 
937  bool OneInputCannotBe(Node* node, Type type) {
938  DCHECK_EQ(2, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
939  return !GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0)).Maybe(type) ||
940  !GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1)).Maybe(type);
941  }
942 
943  void ChangeToDeadValue(Node* node, Node* effect, Node* control) {
944  DCHECK(TypeOf(node).IsNone());
945  // If the node is unreachable, insert an Unreachable node and mark the
946  // value dead.
947  // TODO(jarin,turbofan) Find a way to unify/merge this insertion with
948  // InsertUnreachableIfNecessary.
949  Node* unreachable = effect =
950  graph()->NewNode(common()->Unreachable(), effect, control);
951  const Operator* dead_value =
952  common()->DeadValue(GetInfo(node)->representation());
953  node->ReplaceInput(0, unreachable);
954  node->TrimInputCount(dead_value->ValueInputCount());
955  ReplaceEffectControlUses(node, effect, control);
956  ChangeOp(node, dead_value);
957  }
958 
959  // This function is a generalization of ChangeToPureOp. It can be used to
960  // replace a node that is part of the effect and control chain by a pure node.
961  void ReplaceWithPureNode(Node* node, Node* pure_node) {
962  DCHECK(pure_node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kPure));
963  if (node->op()->EffectInputCount() > 0) {
964  DCHECK_LT(0, node->op()->ControlInputCount());
965  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
966  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
967  if (TypeOf(node).IsNone()) {
968  ChangeToDeadValue(node, effect, control);
969  return;
970  }
971  // Rewire the effect and control chains.
972  ReplaceEffectControlUses(node, effect, control);
973  } else {
974  DCHECK_EQ(0, node->op()->ControlInputCount());
975  }
976  DeferReplacement(node, pure_node);
977  }
978 
979  void ChangeToPureOp(Node* node, const Operator* new_op) {
980  DCHECK(new_op->HasProperty(Operator::kPure));
981  DCHECK_EQ(new_op->ValueInputCount(), node->op()->ValueInputCount());
982  if (node->op()->EffectInputCount() > 0) {
983  DCHECK_LT(0, node->op()->ControlInputCount());
984  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
985  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
986  if (TypeOf(node).IsNone()) {
987  ChangeToDeadValue(node, effect, control);
988  return;
989  }
990  // Rewire the effect and control chains.
991  node->TrimInputCount(new_op->ValueInputCount());
992  ReplaceEffectControlUses(node, effect, control);
993  } else {
994  DCHECK_EQ(0, node->op()->ControlInputCount());
995  }
996  ChangeOp(node, new_op);
997  }
998 
999  void ChangeUnaryToPureBinaryOp(Node* node, const Operator* new_op,
1000  int new_input_index, Node* new_input) {
1001  DCHECK(new_op->HasProperty(Operator::kPure));
1002  DCHECK_EQ(new_op->ValueInputCount(), 2);
1003  DCHECK_EQ(node->op()->ValueInputCount(), 1);
1004  DCHECK_LE(0, new_input_index);
1005  DCHECK_LE(new_input_index, 1);
1006  if (node->op()->EffectInputCount() > 0) {
1007  DCHECK_LT(0, node->op()->ControlInputCount());
1008  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
1009  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
1010  if (TypeOf(node).IsNone()) {
1011  ChangeToDeadValue(node, effect, control);
1012  return;
1013  }
1014  node->TrimInputCount(node->op()->ValueInputCount());
1015  ReplaceEffectControlUses(node, effect, control);
1016  } else {
1017  DCHECK_EQ(0, node->op()->ControlInputCount());
1018  }
1019  if (new_input_index == 0) {
1020  node->InsertInput(jsgraph_->zone(), 0, new_input);
1021  } else {
1022  DCHECK_EQ(new_input_index, 1);
1023  DCHECK_EQ(node->InputCount(), 1);
1024  node->AppendInput(jsgraph_->zone(), new_input);
1025  }
1026  ChangeOp(node, new_op);
1027  }
1028 
1029  // Converts input {index} of {node} according to given UseInfo {use},
1030  // assuming the type of the input is {input_type}. If {input_type} is null,
1031  // it takes the input from the input node {TypeOf(node->InputAt(index))}.
1032  void ConvertInput(Node* node, int index, UseInfo use,
1033  Type input_type = Type::Invalid()) {
1034  // In the change phase, insert a change before the use if necessary.
1035  if (use.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kNone)
1036  return; // No input requirement on the use.
1037  Node* input = node->InputAt(index);
1038  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(input);
1039  NodeInfo* input_info = GetInfo(input);
1040  MachineRepresentation input_rep = input_info->representation();
1041  if (input_rep != use.representation() ||
1042  use.type_check() != TypeCheckKind::kNone) {
1043  // Output representation doesn't match usage.
1044  TRACE(" change: #%d:%s(@%d #%d:%s) ", node->id(), node->op()->mnemonic(),
1045  index, input->id(), input->op()->mnemonic());
1046  TRACE("from %s to %s:%s\n",
1047  MachineReprToString(input_info->representation()),
1048  MachineReprToString(use.representation()),
1049  use.truncation().description());
1050  if (input_type.IsInvalid()) {
1051  input_type = TypeOf(input);
1052  } else {
1053  // This case is reached when ConvertInput is called for TypeGuard nodes
1054  // which explicitly set the {input_type} for their input. In order to
1055  // correctly verify the resulting graph, we have to preserve this
1056  // forced type for the verifier.
1057  DCHECK_EQ(node->opcode(), IrOpcode::kTypeGuard);
1058  input = InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(input_type, input);
1059  }
1060  Node* n = changer_->GetRepresentationFor(input, input_rep, input_type,
1061  node, use);
1062  node->ReplaceInput(index, n);
1063  }
1064  }
1065 
1066  template <Phase T>
1067  void ProcessInput(Node* node, int index, UseInfo use);
1068 
1069  // Just assert for Retype and Lower. Propagate specialized below.
1070  template <Phase T>
1071  void ProcessRemainingInputs(Node* node, int index) {
1072  static_assert(retype<T>() || lower<T>(),
1073  "This version of ProcessRemainingInputs has to be called in "
1074  "the Retype or Lower phase.");
1075  DCHECK_GE(index, NodeProperties::PastValueIndex(node));
1076  DCHECK_GE(index, NodeProperties::PastContextIndex(node));
1077  }
1078 
1079  // Marks node as a possible revisit since it is a use of input that will be
1080  // visited before input is visited.
1081  void MarkAsPossibleRevisit(Node* node, Node* input) {
1082  auto it = might_need_revisit_.find(input);
1083  if (it == might_need_revisit_.end()) {
1084  it = might_need_revisit_.insert({input, ZoneVector<Node*>(zone())}).first;
1085  }
1086  it->second.push_back(node);
1087  TRACE(" Marking #%d: %s as needing revisit due to #%d: %s\n", node->id(),
1088  node->op()->mnemonic(), input->id(), input->op()->mnemonic());
1089  }
1090 
1091  // Just assert for Retype. Propagate and Lower specialized below.
1092  template <Phase T>
1093  void VisitInputs(Node* node) {
1094  static_assert(
1095  retype<T>(),
1096  "This version of VisitInputs has to be called in the Retype phase.");
1097  }
1098 
1099  template <Phase T>
1100  void VisitReturn(Node* node) {
1101  int first_effect_index = NodeProperties::FirstEffectIndex(node);
1102  // Visit integer slot count to pop
1103  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
1104 
1105  // Visit value, context and frame state inputs as tagged.
1106  for (int i = 1; i < first_effect_index; i++) {
1107  ProcessInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1108  }
1109  // Only enqueue other inputs (effects, control).
1110  for (int i = first_effect_index; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
1111  EnqueueInput<T>(node, i);
1112  }
1113  }
1114 
1115  // Helper for an unused node.
1116  template <Phase T>
1117  void VisitUnused(Node* node) {
1118  int first_effect_index = NodeProperties::FirstEffectIndex(node);
1119  for (int i = 0; i < first_effect_index; i++) {
1120  ProcessInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::None());
1121  }
1122  ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, first_effect_index);
1123 
1124  if (lower<T>()) {
1125  TRACE("disconnecting unused #%d:%s\n", node->id(),
1126  node->op()->mnemonic());
1127  DisconnectFromEffectAndControl(node);
1128  node->NullAllInputs(); // Node is now dead.
1129  DeferReplacement(node, graph()->NewNode(common()->Plug()));
1130  }
1131  }
1132 
1133  // Helper for no-op node.
1134  template <Phase T>
1135  void VisitNoop(Node* node, Truncation truncation) {
1136  if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
1137  MachineRepresentation representation =
1138  GetOutputInfoForPhi(TypeOf(node), truncation);
1139  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo(representation, truncation), representation);
1140  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
1141  }
1142 
1143  // Helper for binops of the R x L -> O variety.
1144  template <Phase T>
1145  void VisitBinop(Node* node, UseInfo left_use, UseInfo right_use,
1146  MachineRepresentation output,
1147  Type restriction_type = Type::Any()) {
1148  DCHECK_EQ(2, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
1149  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, left_use);
1150  ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, right_use);
1151  for (int i = 2; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
1152  EnqueueInput<T>(node, i);
1153  }
1154  SetOutput<T>(node, output, restriction_type);
1155  }
1156 
1157  // Helper for binops of the I x I -> O variety.
1158  template <Phase T>
1159  void VisitBinop(Node* node, UseInfo input_use, MachineRepresentation output,
1160  Type restriction_type = Type::Any()) {
1161  VisitBinop<T>(node, input_use, input_use, output, restriction_type);
1162  }
1163 
1164  template <Phase T>
1165  void VisitSpeculativeInt32Binop(Node* node) {
1166  DCHECK_EQ(2, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
1167  if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::NumberOrOddball())) {
1168  return VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1169  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1170  }
1171  NumberOperationHint hint = NumberOperationHintOf(node->op());
1172  return VisitBinop<T>(node,
1173  CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros),
1174  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1175  }

1177  // Helper for unops of the I -> O variety.
1178  template <Phase T>
1179  void VisitUnop(Node* node, UseInfo input_use, MachineRepresentation output,
1180  Type restriction_type = Type::Any()) {
1181  DCHECK_EQ(1, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
1182  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, input_use);
1183  ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 1);
1184  SetOutput<T>(node, output, restriction_type);
1185  }

1187  // Helper for leaf nodes.

1189  void VisitLeaf(Node* node, MachineRepresentation output) {
1190  DCHECK_EQ(0, node->InputCount());
1191  SetOutput<T>(node, output);
1192  }

1199  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
1200  }
1201 
1202  template <Phase T>

1207  template <Phase T>

1213  // Infer representation for phi-like nodes.
1214  MachineRepresentation GetOutputInfoForPhi(Type type, Truncation use) {
1215  // Compute the representation.
1216  if (type.Is(Type::None())) {
1217  return MachineRepresentation::kNone;
1218  } else if (type.Is(Type::Signed32()) || type.Is(Type::Unsigned32())) {
1219  return MachineRepresentation::kWord32;
1220  } else if (type.Is(Type::NumberOrOddball()) && use.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
1221  return MachineRepresentation::kWord32;
1222  } else if (type.Is(Type::Boolean())) {
1223  return MachineRepresentation::kBit;
1224  } else if (type.Is(Type::NumberOrOddball()) &&
1225  use.TruncatesOddballAndBigIntToNumber()) {
1226  return MachineRepresentation::kFloat64;
1227  } else if (type.Is(Type::Union(Type::SignedSmall(), Type::NaN(), zone()))) {
1228  // TODO(turbofan): For Phis that return either NaN or some Smi, it's
1229  // beneficial to not go all the way to double, unless the uses are
1230  // double uses. For tagging that just means some potentially expensive
1231  // allocation code; we might want to do the same for -0 as well?
1232  return MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
1233  } else if (type.Is(Type::Number())) {
1234  return MachineRepresentation::kFloat64;
1235  } else if (type.Is(Type::BigInt()) && Is64() && use.IsUsedAsWord64()) {
1236  return MachineRepresentation::kWord64;
1237  } else if (type.Is(Type::ExternalPointer()) ||
1238  type.Is(Type::SandboxedPointer())) {
1239  return MachineType::PointerRepresentation();
1240  }
1241  return MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
1242  }
1243 
1244  // Helper for handling selects.
1245  template <Phase T>
1246  void VisitSelect(Node* node, Truncation truncation,
1247  SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1248  DCHECK(TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Boolean()));
1249  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Bool());
1250 
1251  MachineRepresentation output =
1252  GetOutputInfoForPhi(TypeOf(node), truncation);
1253  SetOutput<T>(node, output);
1254 
1255  if (lower<T>()) {
1256  // Update the select operator.
1257  SelectParameters p = SelectParametersOf(node->op());
1258  if (output != p.representation()) {
1259  ChangeOp(node, lowering->common()->Select(output, p.hint()));
1260  }
1261  }
1262  // Convert inputs to the output representation of this phi, pass the
1263  // truncation truncation along.
1264  UseInfo input_use(output, truncation);
1265  ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, input_use);
1266  ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, input_use);
1267  }
1268 
1269  // Helper for handling phis.
1270  template <Phase T>
1271  void VisitPhi(Node* node, Truncation truncation,
1272  SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1273  // If we already have a non-tagged representation set in the Phi node, it
1274  // does come from subgraphs using machine operators we introduced early in
1275  // the pipeline. In this case, we just keep the representation.
1276  MachineRepresentation output = PhiRepresentationOf(node->op());
1277  if (output == MachineRepresentation::kTagged) {
1278  output = GetOutputInfoForPhi(TypeOf(node), truncation);
1279  }
1280  // Only set the output representation if not running with type
1281  // feedback. (Feedback typing will set the representation.)
1282  SetOutput<T>(node, output);
1283 
1284  int values = node->op()->ValueInputCount();
1285  if (lower<T>()) {
1286  // Update the phi operator.
1287  if (output != PhiRepresentationOf(node->op())) {
1288  ChangeOp(node, lowering->common()->Phi(output, values));
1289  }
1290  }
1291 
1292  // Convert inputs to the output representation of this phi, pass the
1293  // truncation along.
1294  UseInfo input_use(output, truncation);
1295  for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
1296  ProcessInput<T>(node, i, i < values ? input_use : UseInfo::None());
1297  }
1298  }
1299 
1300  template <Phase T>
1301  void VisitObjectIs(Node* node, Type type, SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1302  Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
1303  if (input_type.Is(type)) {
1304  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::None(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
1305  if (lower<T>()) {
1306  DeferReplacement(
1307  node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
1308  true_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(1)));
1309  }
1310  } else {
1311  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
1312  if (lower<T>() && !input_type.Maybe(type)) {
1313  DeferReplacement(
1314  node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
1315  false_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0)));
1316  }
1317  }
1318  }
1319 
1320  template <Phase T>
1321  void VisitCheck(Node* node, Type type, SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1322  if (InputIs(node, type)) {
1323  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
1324  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
1325  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
1326  } else {
1327  VisitUnop<T>(node,
1328  UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource()),
1329  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
1330  }
1331  }
1332 
1333  template <Phase T>
1334  void VisitCall(Node* node, SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1335  auto call_descriptor = CallDescriptorOf(node->op());
1336  int params = static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->ParameterCount());
1337  int value_input_count = node->op()->ValueInputCount();
1338 
1339  DCHECK_GT(value_input_count, 0);
1340  DCHECK_GE(value_input_count, params);
1341 
1342  // The target of the call.
1343  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Any());
1344 
1345  // For the parameters (indexes [1, ..., params]), propagate representation
1346  // information from call descriptor.
1347  for (int i = 1; i <= params; i++) {
1348  ProcessInput<T>(node, i,
1349  TruncatingUseInfoFromRepresentation(
1350  call_descriptor->GetInputType(i).representation()));
1351  }
1352 
1353  // Rest of the value inputs.
1354  for (int i = params + 1; i < value_input_count; i++) {
1355  ProcessInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1356  }
1357 
1358  // Effect and Control.
1359  ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, value_input_count);
1360 
1361  if (call_descriptor->ReturnCount() > 0) {
1362  SetOutput<T>(node, call_descriptor->GetReturnType(0).representation());
1363  } else {
1364  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1365  }
1366  }
1367 
1368  void MaskShiftOperand(Node* node, Type rhs_type) {
1369  if (!rhs_type.Is(type_cache_->kZeroToThirtyOne)) {
1370  Node* const rhs = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
1371  node->ReplaceInput(1,
1372  graph()->NewNode(jsgraph_->machine()->Word32And(), rhs,
1373  jsgraph_->Int32Constant(0x1F)));
1374  }
1375  }
1376 
1377  static MachineSemantic DeoptValueSemanticOf(Type type) {
1378  // We only need signedness to do deopt correctly.
1379  if (type.Is(Type::Signed32())) {
1380  return MachineSemantic::kInt32;
1381  } else if (type.Is(Type::Unsigned32())) {
1382  return MachineSemantic::kUint32;
1383  } else {
1384  return MachineSemantic::kAny;
1385  }
1386  }
1387 
1388  static MachineType DeoptMachineTypeOf(MachineRepresentation rep, Type type) {
1389  if (type.IsNone()) {
1390  return MachineType::None();
1391  }
1392  // Do not distinguish between various Tagged variations.
1393  if (IsAnyTagged(rep)) {
1394  return MachineType::AnyTagged();
1395  }
1396  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
1397  if (type.Is(Type::SignedBigInt64())) {
1398  return MachineType::SignedBigInt64();
1399  }
1400 
1401  if (type.Is(Type::UnsignedBigInt64())) {
1402  return MachineType::UnsignedBigInt64();
1403  }
1404 
1405  if (type.Is(Type::BigInt())) {
1406  return MachineType::AnyTagged();
1407  }
1408 
1409  DCHECK(type.Is(TypeCache::Get()->kSafeInteger));
1410  return MachineType(rep, MachineSemantic::kInt64);
1411  }
1412  MachineType machine_type(rep, DeoptValueSemanticOf(type));
1413  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
1414  machine_type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord32,
1415  machine_type.semantic() == MachineSemantic::kInt32 ||
1416  machine_type.semantic() == MachineSemantic::kUint32);
1417  DCHECK_IMPLIES(machine_type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kBit,
1418  type.Is(Type::Boolean()));
1419  return machine_type;
1420  }
1421 
1422  template <Phase T>
1423  void VisitStateValues(Node* node) {
1424  if (propagate<T>()) {
1425  for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
1426  if (IsLargeBigInt(TypeOf(node->InputAt(i)))) {
1427  // BigInt64s are rematerialized in deoptimization. The other BigInts
1428  // must be rematerialized before deoptimization. By propagating an
1429  // AnyTagged use, the RepresentationChanger is going to insert the
1430  // necessary conversions.
1431  EnqueueInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1432  } else if (IsLoadFloat16ArrayElement(node->InputAt(i))) {
1433  // Loads from Float16Arrays are raw bits as word16s but have the
1434  // Number type, since not all archs have native float16
1435  // representation. Rematerialize them as float64s in deoptimization.
1436  EnqueueInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::Float64());
1437  } else {
1438  EnqueueInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::Any());
1439  }
1440  }
1441  } else if (lower<T>()) {
1442  Zone* zone = jsgraph_->zone();
1443  ZoneVector<MachineType>* types =
1444  zone->New<ZoneVector<MachineType>>(node->InputCount(), zone);
1445  for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
1446  Node* input = node->InputAt(i);
1447  MachineRepresentation input_rep = GetInfo(input)->representation();
1448  if (IsLargeBigInt(TypeOf(input))) {
1449  ConvertInput(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1450  } else if (IsLoadFloat16ArrayElement(input)) {
1451  ConvertInput(node, i, UseInfo::Float64());
1452  input_rep = MachineRepresentation::kFloat64;
1453  }
1454  (*types)[i] = DeoptMachineTypeOf(input_rep, TypeOf(input));
1455  }
1456  SparseInputMask mask = SparseInputMaskOf(node->op());
1457  ChangeOp(node, common()->TypedStateValues(types, mask));
1458  }
1459  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1460  }
1461 
1462  template <Phase T>
1463  void VisitFrameState(FrameState node) {
1464  DCHECK_EQ(5, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
1465  DCHECK_EQ(1, OperatorProperties::GetFrameStateInputCount(node->op()));
1466  DCHECK_EQ(FrameState::kFrameStateInputCount, node->InputCount());
1467 
1468  ProcessInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateParametersInput,
1469  UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1470  ProcessInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateLocalsInput,
1471  UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1472 
1473  // Accumulator is a special flower - we need to remember its type in
1474  // a singleton typed-state-values node (as if it was a singleton
1475  // state-values node).
1476  Node* accumulator = node.stack();
1477  if (propagate<T>()) {
1478  if (IsLargeBigInt(TypeOf(accumulator))) {
1479  EnqueueInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateStackInput,
1480  UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1481  } else if (IsLoadFloat16ArrayElement(accumulator)) {
1482  EnqueueInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateStackInput,
1483  UseInfo::Float64());
1484  } else {
1485  EnqueueInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateStackInput,
1486  UseInfo::Any());
1487  }
1488  } else if (lower<T>()) {
1489  MachineRepresentation accumulator_rep =
1490  GetInfo(accumulator)->representation();
1491  Type accumulator_type = TypeOf(accumulator);
1492  if (IsLargeBigInt(accumulator_type)) {
1493  ConvertInput(node, FrameState::kFrameStateStackInput,
1494  UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1495  accumulator = node.stack();
1496  } else if (IsLoadFloat16ArrayElement(accumulator)) {
1497  ConvertInput(node, FrameState::kFrameStateStackInput,
1498  UseInfo::Float64());
1499  accumulator = node.stack();
1500  accumulator_rep = MachineRepresentation::kFloat64;
1501  }
1502  Zone* zone = jsgraph_->zone();
1503  if (accumulator == jsgraph_->OptimizedOutConstant()) {
1504  node->ReplaceInput(FrameState::kFrameStateStackInput,
1505  jsgraph_->SingleDeadTypedStateValues());
1506  } else {
1507  ZoneVector<MachineType>* types =
1508  zone->New<ZoneVector<MachineType>>(1, zone);
1509  (*types)[0] = DeoptMachineTypeOf(accumulator_rep, accumulator_type);
1510 
1511  node->ReplaceInput(
1512  FrameState::kFrameStateStackInput,
1513  jsgraph_->graph()->NewNode(
1514  common()->TypedStateValues(types, SparseInputMask::Dense()),
1515  node.stack()));
1516  }
1517  }
1518 
1519  ProcessInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateContextInput,
1520  UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1521  ProcessInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateFunctionInput,
1522  UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1523  ProcessInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateOuterStateInput,
1524  UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1525  return SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1526  }
1527 
1528  template <Phase T>
1529  void VisitObjectState(Node* node) {
1530  if (propagate<T>()) {
1531  for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
1532  if (IsLargeBigInt(TypeOf(node->InputAt(i)))) {
1533  EnqueueInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1534  } else if (IsLoadFloat16ArrayElement(node->InputAt(i))) {
1535  EnqueueInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::Float64());
1536  } else {
1537  EnqueueInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::Any());
1538  }
1539  }
1540  } else if (lower<T>()) {
1541  Zone* zone = jsgraph_->zone();
1542  ZoneVector<MachineType>* types =
1543  zone->New<ZoneVector<MachineType>>(node->InputCount(), zone);
1544  for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
1545  Node* input = node->InputAt(i);
1546  MachineRepresentation input_rep = GetInfo(input)->representation();
1547  if (IsLargeBigInt(TypeOf(input))) {
1548  ConvertInput(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1549  } else if (IsLoadFloat16ArrayElement(input)) {
1550  ConvertInput(node, i, UseInfo::Float64());
1551  input_rep = MachineRepresentation::kFloat64;
1552  }
1553  (*types)[i] = DeoptMachineTypeOf(input_rep, TypeOf(input));
1554  }
1555  ChangeOp(node, common()->TypedObjectState(ObjectIdOf(node->op()), types));
1556  }
1557  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1558  }
