1595 
1596  WriteBarrierKind WriteBarrierKindFor(
1597  BaseTaggedness base_taggedness,
1598  MachineRepresentation field_representation, Type field_type,
1599  MachineRepresentation value_representation, Node* value) {
1600  if (base_taggedness == kTaggedBase &&
1601  CanBeTaggedPointer(field_representation)) {
1602  Type value_type = NodeProperties::GetType(value);
1603  if (value_representation == MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned) {
1604  // Write barriers are only for stores of heap objects.
1605  return kNoWriteBarrier;
1606  }
1607  if (field_type.Is(Type::BooleanOrNullOrUndefined()) ||
1608  value_type.Is(Type::BooleanOrNullOrUndefined())) {
1609  // Write barriers are not necessary when storing true, false, null or
1610  // undefined, because these special oddballs are always in the root set.
1611  return kNoWriteBarrier;
1612  }
1613  if (value_type.IsHeapConstant()) {
1614  RootIndex root_index;
1615  const RootsTable& roots_table = jsgraph_->isolate()->roots_table();
1616  if (roots_table.IsRootHandle(value_type.AsHeapConstant()->Value(),
1617  &root_index)) {
1618  if (RootsTable::IsImmortalImmovable(root_index)) {
1619  // Write barriers are unnecessary for immortal immovable roots.
1620  return kNoWriteBarrier;
1621  }
1622  }
1623  }
1624  if (field_representation == MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer ||
1625  value_representation == MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer) {
1626  // Write barriers for heap objects are cheaper.
1627  return kPointerWriteBarrier;
1628  }
1629  NumberMatcher m(value);
1630  if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
1631  if (IsSmiDouble(m.ResolvedValue())) {
1632  // Storing a smi doesn't need a write barrier.
1633  return kNoWriteBarrier;
1634  }
1635  // The NumberConstant will be represented as HeapNumber.
1636  return kPointerWriteBarrier;
1637  }
1638  return kFullWriteBarrier;
1639  }
1640  return kNoWriteBarrier;
1641  }
1642 
1643  WriteBarrierKind WriteBarrierKindFor(
1644  BaseTaggedness base_taggedness,
1645  MachineRepresentation field_representation, int field_offset,
1646  Type field_type, MachineRepresentation value_representation,
1647  Node* value) {
1648  WriteBarrierKind write_barrier_kind =
1649  WriteBarrierKindFor(base_taggedness, field_representation, field_type,
1650  value_representation, value);
1651  if (write_barrier_kind != kNoWriteBarrier) {
1652  if (base_taggedness == kTaggedBase &&
1653  field_offset == HeapObject::kMapOffset) {
1654  write_barrier_kind = kMapWriteBarrier;
1655  }
1656  }
1657  return write_barrier_kind;
1658  }
1659 
1660  TFGraph* graph() const { return jsgraph_->graph(); }
1661  CommonOperatorBuilder* common() const { return jsgraph_->common(); }
1662  SimplifiedOperatorBuilder* simplified() const {
1663  return jsgraph_->simplified();
1664  }
1665 
1666  template <Phase T>
1667  void VisitForCheckedInt32Mul(Node* node, Truncation truncation,
1668  Type input0_type, Type input1_type,
1669  UseInfo input_use) {
1670  DCHECK_EQ(node->opcode(), IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberMultiply);
1671  // A -0 input is impossible or will cause a deopt.
1672  DCHECK(BothInputsAre(node, Type::Signed32()) ||
1673  !input_use.truncation().IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero());
1674 
1675  CheckForMinusZeroMode mz_mode;
1676  Type restriction;
1677  if (IsSomePositiveOrderedNumber(input0_type) ||
1678  IsSomePositiveOrderedNumber(input1_type)) {
1679  mz_mode = CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero;
1680  restriction = Type::Signed32();
1681  } else if (truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero()) {
1682  mz_mode = CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero;
1683  restriction = Type::Signed32OrMinusZero();
1684  } else {
1685  mz_mode = CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero;
1686  restriction = Type::Signed32();
1687  }
1688 
1689  VisitBinop<T>(node, input_use, MachineRepresentation::kWord32, restriction);
1690  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, simplified()->CheckedInt32Mul(mz_mode));
1691  }
1692 
1693  void ChangeToInt32OverflowOp(Node* node) {
1694  ChangeOp(node, Int32OverflowOp(node));
1695  }
1696 
1697  void ChangeToUint32OverflowOp(Node* node) {
1698  ChangeOp(node, Uint32OverflowOp(node));
1699  }
1700 
1701  template <Phase T>
1702  void VisitSpeculativeSmallIntegerAdditiveOp(Node* node, Truncation truncation,
1703  SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1704  Type left_upper = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0));
1705  Type right_upper = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
1706 
1707  if (left_upper.Is(type_cache_->kAdditiveSafeIntegerOrMinusZero) &&
1708  right_upper.Is(type_cache_->kAdditiveSafeIntegerOrMinusZero)) {
1709  // Only eliminate the node if its typing rule can be satisfied, namely
1710  // that a safe integer is produced.
1711  if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
1712 
1713  // If we know how to interpret the result or if the users only care
1714  // about the low 32-bits, we can truncate to Word32 do a wrapping
1715  // addition.
1716  if (GetUpperBound(node).Is(Type::Signed32()) ||
1717  GetUpperBound(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) ||
1718  truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
1719  // => Int32Add/Sub
1720  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
1721  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
1722  return;
1723  }
1724  }
1725 
1726  // Try to use type feedback.
1727  NumberOperationHint const hint = NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall;
1728  DCHECK_EQ(hint, NumberOperationHintOf(node->op()));
1729 
1730  Type left_feedback_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
1731  Type right_feedback_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
1732 
1733  // Using Signed32 as restriction type amounts to promising there won't be
1734  // signed overflow. This is incompatible with relying on a Word32 truncation
1735  // in order to skip the overflow check. Similarly, we must not drop -0 from
1736  // the result type unless we deopt for -0 inputs.
1737  Type const restriction =
1738  truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()
1739  ? Type::Any()
1740  : (truncation.identify_zeros() == kIdentifyZeros)
1741  ? Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()
1742  : Type::Signed32();
1743 
1744  // Handle the case when no int32 checks on inputs are necessary (but
1745  // an overflow check is needed on the output). Note that we do not
1746  // have to do any check if at most one side can be minus zero. For
1747  // subtraction we need to handle the case of -0 - 0 properly, since
1748  // that can produce -0.
1749  Type left_constraint_type =
1750  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kSpeculativeSmallIntegerAdd
1751  ? Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()
1752  : Type::Signed32();
1753  if (left_upper.Is(left_constraint_type) &&
1754  right_upper.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
1755  (left_upper.Is(Type::Signed32()) || right_upper.Is(Type::Signed32()))) {
1756  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1757  MachineRepresentation::kWord32, restriction);
1758  } else {
1759  // If the output's truncation is identify-zeros, we can pass it
1760  // along. Moreover, if the operation is addition and we know the
1761  // right-hand side is not minus zero, we do not have to distinguish
1762  // between 0 and -0.
1763  IdentifyZeros left_identify_zeros = truncation.identify_zeros();
1764  if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kSpeculativeSmallIntegerAdd &&
1765  !right_feedback_type.Maybe(Type::MinusZero())) {
1766  left_identify_zeros = kIdentifyZeros;
1767  }
1768  UseInfo left_use =
1769  CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, left_identify_zeros);
1770  // For CheckedInt32Add and CheckedInt32Sub, we don't need to do
1771  // a minus zero check for the right hand side, since we already
1772  // know that the left hand side is a proper Signed32 value,
1773  // potentially guarded by a check.
1774  UseInfo right_use = CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros);
1775  VisitBinop<T>(node, left_use, right_use, MachineRepresentation::kWord32,
1776  restriction);
1777  }
1778 
1779  if (lower<T>()) {
1780  if (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
1781  !CanOverflowSigned32(node->op(), left_feedback_type,
1782  right_feedback_type, type_cache_,
1783  graph_zone())) {
1784  ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
1785  } else {
1786  ChangeToInt32OverflowOp(node);
1787  }
1788  }
1789  }
1790 
1791  bool CanSpeculateAdditiveSafeInteger(Node* node) {
1792  if (!v8_flags.additive_safe_int_feedback) return false;
1793  if (NumberOperationHintOf(node->op()) !=
1794  NumberOperationHint::kAdditiveSafeInteger) {
1795  return false;
1796  }
1797  DCHECK_EQ(2, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
1798  // Only speculate AdditiveSafeInteger if one of the sides are already known
1799  // to be in the AdditiveSafeInteger range, since the check is relatively
1800  // expensive.
1801  Type lhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
1802  Type rhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
1803  return lhs_type.Is(type_cache_->kAdditiveSafeInteger) ||
1804  rhs_type.Is(type_cache_->kAdditiveSafeInteger);
1805  }
1806 
1807  template <Phase T>
1808  void VisitSpeculativeAdditiveOp(Node* node, Truncation truncation,
1809  SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1810  if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::Integral32OrMinusZero())) {
1811  if (GetUpperBound(node).Is(Type::Signed32()) ||
1812  GetUpperBound(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) ||
1813  truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
1814  // => Int32Add/Sub
1815  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1816  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1817  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
1818  return;
1819  }
1820 
1821  // TODO(victorgomes): Simplify this to a Word64Add. We don't need the
1822  // additive safe integer range check, since we know inputs are Integral32.
1823  if (v8_flags.additive_safe_int_feedback &&
1824  NumberOperationHintOf(node->op()) ==
1825  NumberOperationHint::kAdditiveSafeInteger) {
1826  // => AdditiveSafeIntegerAdd/Sub
1827  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::CheckedSafeIntAsWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
1828  MachineRepresentation::kWord64,
1829  type_cache_->kAdditiveSafeInteger);
1830  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, AdditiveSafeIntegerOverflowOp(node));
1831  return;
1832  }
1833  }
1834 
1835  if (CanSpeculateAdditiveSafeInteger(node)) {
1836  if (truncation.IsUnused()) {
1837  if (lower<T>() && TypeOf(node).IsNone()) {
1838  DeferReplacement(
1839  node, InsertUnconditionalDeopt(
1840  node, DeoptimizeReason::kNotAdditiveSafeInteger));
1841  }
1842  return VisitUnused<T>(node);
1843  }
1844 
1845  if (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() && !TypeOf(node).IsNone()) {
1846  // This case handles addition where the result might be truncated to
1847  // word32. Even if the inputs might be larger than 2^32, we can safely
1848  // perform 32-bit addition *here* if the inputs are in the additive
1849  // safe range. We *must* propagate the CheckedSafeIntTruncatingWord32
1850  // information. This is because we need to ensure that we deoptimize
1851  // if either input is not an integer, or not in the range.
1852  // => Int32Add/Sub
1853  VisitBinop<T>(node,
1854  UseInfo::CheckedSafeIntTruncatingWord32(FeedbackSource{}),
1855  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1856  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
1857  return;
1858  }
1859 
1860  // => AdditiveSafeIntegerAdd/Sub
1861  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::CheckedSafeIntAsWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
1862  MachineRepresentation::kWord64,
1863  type_cache_->kAdditiveSafeInteger);
1864  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, AdditiveSafeIntegerOverflowOp(node));
1865  return;
1866  }
1867 
1868  // Default case => Float64Add/Sub
1869  VisitBinop<T>(node,
1870  UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(kDistinguishZeros,
1871  FeedbackSource()),
1872  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, Type::Number());
1873  if (lower<T>()) {
1874  ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
1875  }
1876  }
1877 
1878  template <Phase T>
1879  void VisitSpeculativeNumberModulus(Node* node, Truncation truncation,
1880  SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1881  if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
1882  (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
1883  NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()))) {
1884  // => unsigned Uint32Mod
1885  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
1886  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Uint32Mod(node));
1887  return;
1888  }
1889  if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::Signed32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
1890  (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
1891  NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Signed32()))) {
1892  // => signed Int32Mod
1893  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
1894  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Mod(node));
1895  return;
1896  }
1897 
1898  // Try to use type feedback.
1899  NumberOperationHint hint = NumberOperationHintOf(node->op());
1900 
1901  // Handle the case when no uint32 checks on inputs are necessary
1902  // (but an overflow check is needed on the output).
1903  if (BothInputsAreUnsigned32(node)) {
1904  if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
1905  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1906  MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Unsigned32());
1907  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToUint32OverflowOp(node);
1908  return;
1909  }
1910  }
1911 
1912  // Handle the case when no int32 checks on inputs are necessary
1913  // (but an overflow check is needed on the output).
1914  if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::Signed32())) {
1915  // If both the inputs the feedback are int32, use the overflow op.
1916  if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
1917  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1918  MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Signed32());
1919  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToInt32OverflowOp(node);
1920  return;
1921  }
1922  }
1923 
1924  if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
1925  // If the result is truncated, we only need to check the inputs.
1926  // For the left hand side we just propagate the identify zeros
1927  // mode of the {truncation}; and for modulus the sign of the
1928  // right hand side doesn't matter anyways, so in particular there's
1929  // no observable difference between a 0 and a -0 then.
1930  UseInfo const lhs_use =
1931  CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, truncation.identify_zeros());
1932  UseInfo const rhs_use =
1933  CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros);
1934  if (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
1935  VisitBinop<T>(node, lhs_use, rhs_use, MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1936  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Mod(node));
1937  } else if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZeroOrNaN())) {
1938  Type const restriction =
1939  truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero() &&
1940  TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Maybe(Type::MinusZero())
1941  ? Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()
1942  : Type::Unsigned32();
1943  VisitBinop<T>(node, lhs_use, rhs_use, MachineRepresentation::kWord32,
1944  restriction);
1945  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToUint32OverflowOp(node);
1946  } else {
1947  Type const restriction =
1948  truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero() &&
1949  TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Maybe(Type::MinusZero())
1950  ? Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()
1951  : Type::Signed32();
1952  VisitBinop<T>(node, lhs_use, rhs_use, MachineRepresentation::kWord32,
1953  restriction);
1954  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToInt32OverflowOp(node);
1955  }
1956  return;
1957  }
1958 
1959  if (TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) &&
1960  TypeOf(node->InputAt(1)).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) &&
1961  (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
1962  NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()))) {
1963  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1964  MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Number());
1965  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Uint32Mod(node));
1966  return;
1967  }
1968  if (TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Signed32()) &&
1969  TypeOf(node->InputAt(1)).Is(Type::Signed32()) &&
1970  (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
1971  NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Signed32()))) {
1972  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1973  MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Number());
1974  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Mod(node));
1975  return;
1976  }
1977 
1978  // default case => Float64Mod
1979  // For the left hand side we just propagate the identify zeros
1980  // mode of the {truncation}; and for modulus the sign of the
1981  // right hand side doesn't matter anyways, so in particular there's
1982  // no observable difference between a 0 and a -0 then.
1983  UseInfo const lhs_use = UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(
1984  truncation.identify_zeros(), FeedbackSource());
1985  UseInfo const rhs_use = UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(
1986  kIdentifyZeros, FeedbackSource());
1987  VisitBinop<T>(node, lhs_use, rhs_use, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64,
1988  Type::Number());
1989  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
1990  }
1991 
1992  // Just assert for Propagate and Retype. Lower specialized below.
1993  template <Phase T>
1994  void InsertUnreachableIfNecessary(Node* node) {
1995  static_assert(propagate<T>() || retype<T>(),
1996  "This version of InsertUnreachableIfNecessary has to be "
1997  "called in the Propagate or Retype phase.");
1998  }
1999 
2000  template <Phase T>
2001  void VisitCheckBounds(Node* node, SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
2002  CheckBoundsParameters const& p = CheckBoundsParametersOf(node->op());
2003  FeedbackSource const& feedback = p.check_parameters().feedback();
2004  Type const index_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
2005  Type const length_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
2006 
2007  const bool allow_64_bit = (p.flags() & CheckBoundsFlag::kAllow64BitBounds);
2008  // Conversions, if requested and needed, will be handled by the
2009  // representation changer, not by the lower-level Checked*Bounds operators.
2010  CheckBoundsFlags new_flags =
2011  p.flags().without(CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero);
2012 
2013  if (length_type.Is(Type::Unsigned31())) {
2014  if (index_type.Is(Type::Integral32()) ||
2015  (index_type.Is(Type::Integral32OrMinusZero()) &&
2016  p.flags() & CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero)) {
2017  // Map the values in the [-2^31,-1] range to the [2^31,2^32-1] range,
2018  // which will be considered out-of-bounds because the {length_type} is
2019  // limited to Unsigned31. This also converts -0 to 0.
2020  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2021  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2022  if (lower<T>()) {
2023  if (index_type.IsNone() || length_type.IsNone() ||
2024  (index_type.Min() >= 0.0 &&
2025  index_type.Max() < length_type.Min())) {
2026  // The bounds check is redundant if we already know that
2027  // the index is within the bounds of [0.0, length[.
2028  // TODO(neis): Move this into TypedOptimization?
2029  if (v8_flags.turbo_typer_hardening) {
2030  new_flags |= CheckBoundsFlag::kAbortOnOutOfBounds;
2031  } else {
2032  DeferReplacement(node, NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0));
2033  return;
2034  }
2035  }
2036  ChangeOp(node,
2037  simplified()->CheckedUint32Bounds(feedback, new_flags));
2038  }
2039  } else if (p.flags() & CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero) {
2040  if (jsgraph_->machine()->Is64()) {
2041  const auto index_use = UseInfo::CheckedTaggedAsArrayIndex(feedback);
2042  const auto bound_use =
2043  allow_64_bit ? UseInfo::Word64() : UseInfo::TruncatingWord32();
2044  VisitBinop<T>(node, index_use, bound_use,
2045  MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
2046  if (lower<T>()) {
2047  if (allow_64_bit) {
2048  ChangeOp(node,
2049  simplified()->CheckedUint64Bounds(feedback, new_flags));
2050  } else {
2051  Node* bound = node->InputAt(1);
2052  Node* zero_extended = graph()->NewNode(
2053  lowering->machine()->ChangeUint32ToUint64(), bound);
2054  node->ReplaceInput(1, zero_extended);
2055  ChangeOp(node,
2056  simplified()->CheckedUint64Bounds(feedback, new_flags));
2057  }
2058  }
2059  } else {
2060  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::CheckedTaggedAsArrayIndex(feedback),
2061  UseInfo::Word(), MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
2062  if (lower<T>()) {
2063  ChangeOp(node,
2064  simplified()->CheckedUint32Bounds(feedback, new_flags));
2065  }
2066  }
2067  } else {
2068  VisitBinop<T>(
2069  node, UseInfo::CheckedSigned32AsWord32(kDistinguishZeros, feedback),
2070  UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(), MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2071  if (lower<T>()) {
2072  ChangeOp(node,
2073  simplified()->CheckedUint32Bounds(feedback, new_flags));
2074  }
2075  }
2076  } else {
2077  CHECK(length_type.Is(type_cache_->kPositiveSafeInteger));
2078  CHECK(allow_64_bit);
2079  IdentifyZeros zero_handling =
2080  (p.flags() & CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero)
2081  ? kIdentifyZeros
2082  : kDistinguishZeros;
2083  VisitBinop<T>(node,
2084  UseInfo::CheckedSigned64AsWord64(zero_handling, feedback),
2085  UseInfo::Word64(), MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
2086  if (lower<T>()) {
2087  ChangeOp(node, simplified()->CheckedUint64Bounds(feedback, new_flags));
2088  }
2089  }
2090  }
2091 
2092  UseInfo UseInfoForFastApiCallArgument(CTypeInfo type,
2093  CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation repr,
2094  FeedbackSource const& feedback) {
2095  START_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
2096  switch (type.GetSequenceType()) {
2097  case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kScalar: {
2098  uint8_t flags = uint8_t(type.GetFlags());
2099  if (flags & uint8_t(CTypeInfo::Flags::kEnforceRangeBit) ||
2100  flags & uint8_t(CTypeInfo::Flags::kClampBit)) {
2101  DCHECK(repr != CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kBigInt);
2102  // If the parameter is marked as `kEnforceRange` or `kClampBit`, then
2103  // special type conversion gets added explicitly to the generated
2104  // code. Therefore it is sufficient here to only require here that the
2105  // value is a Float64, even though the C++ signature actually asks for
2106  // an `int32_t`.
2107  return UseInfo::CheckedNumberAsFloat64(kIdentifyZeros, feedback);
2108  }
2109  switch (type.GetType()) {
2110  case CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid:
2111  case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint8:
2112  UNREACHABLE();
2113  case CTypeInfo::Type::kBool:
2114  return UseInfo::Bool();
2115  case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt32:
2116  case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint32:
2117  return UseInfo::CheckedNumberAsWord32(feedback);
2118  // TODO(mslekova): We deopt for unsafe integers, but ultimately we
2119  // want to make this less restrictive in order to stay on the fast
2120  // path.
2121  case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt64:
2122  case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint64:
2123  if (repr == CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kBigInt) {
2124  return UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(feedback);
2125  } else if (repr == CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kNumber) {
2126  return UseInfo::CheckedSigned64AsWord64(kIdentifyZeros, feedback);
2127  } else {
2128  UNREACHABLE();
2129  }
2130  case CTypeInfo::Type::kAny:
2131  return UseInfo::CheckedSigned64AsWord64(kIdentifyZeros, feedback);
2132  case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat32:
2133  case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat64:
2134  return UseInfo::CheckedNumberAsFloat64(kDistinguishZeros, feedback);
2135  case CTypeInfo::Type::kPointer:
2136  case CTypeInfo::Type::kV8Value:
2137  case CTypeInfo::Type::kSeqOneByteString:
2138  case CTypeInfo::Type::kApiObject:
2139  return UseInfo::AnyTagged();
2140  }
2141  }
2142  case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsSequence: {
2143  CHECK_EQ(type.GetType(), CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid);
2144  return UseInfo::AnyTagged();
2145  }
2146  default: {
2147  UNREACHABLE(); // TODO(mslekova): Implement array buffers.
2148  }
2149  }
2150  END_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
2151  }
2152 
2153  static constexpr int kInitialArgumentsCount = 10;
2154 
2155  template <Phase T>
2156  void VisitFastApiCall(Node* node, SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
2157  FastApiCallParameters const& op_params =
2158  FastApiCallParametersOf(node->op());
2159  // We only consider the first function signature here. In case of function
2160  // overloads, we only support the case of two functions that differ for one
2161  // argument, which must be a JSArray in one function and a TypedArray in the
2162  // other function, and both JSArrays and TypedArrays have the same UseInfo
2163  // UseInfo::AnyTagged(). All the other argument types must match.
2164  const CFunctionInfo* c_signature = op_params.c_function().signature;
2165  const int c_arg_count = c_signature->ArgumentCount();
2166  CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = op_params.descriptor();
2167  // Arguments for CallApiCallbackOptimizedXXX builtin (including context)
2168  // plus JS arguments (including receiver).
2169  int slow_arg_count = static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->ParameterCount());
2170  const int value_input_count = node->op()->ValueInputCount();
2171  CHECK_EQ(FastApiCallNode::ArityForArgc(c_arg_count, slow_arg_count),
2172  value_input_count);
2173 
2174  FastApiCallNode n(node);
2175 
2176  base::SmallVector<UseInfo, kInitialArgumentsCount> arg_use_info(
2177  c_arg_count);
2178  // Propagate representation information from TypeInfo.
2179  int cursor = 0;
2180  for (int i = 0; i < c_arg_count; i++) {
2181  arg_use_info[i] = UseInfoForFastApiCallArgument(
2182  c_signature->ArgumentInfo(i), c_signature->GetInt64Representation(),
2183  op_params.feedback());
2184  ProcessInput<T>(node, cursor++, arg_use_info[i]);
2185  }
2186  // Callback data for fast call.
2187  DCHECK_EQ(n.CallbackDataIndex(), cursor);
2188  ProcessInput<T>(node, cursor++, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
2189 
2190  // The call code for the slow call.
2191  ProcessInput<T>(node, cursor++, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
2192  // For the slow builtin parameters (indexes [1, ..., params]), propagate
2193  // representation information from call descriptor.
2194  for (int i = 1; i <= slow_arg_count; i++) {
2195  ProcessInput<T>(node, cursor++,
2196  TruncatingUseInfoFromRepresentation(
2197  call_descriptor->GetInputType(i).representation()));
2198  }
2199  // Visit frame state input as tagged.
2200  DCHECK_EQ(n.FrameStateIndex(), cursor);
2201  ProcessInput<T>(node, cursor++, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
2202  DCHECK_EQ(cursor, value_input_count);
2203 
2204  // Effect and Control.
2205  ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, value_input_count);
2206 
2207  CTypeInfo return_type = op_params.c_function().signature->ReturnInfo();
2208  switch (return_type.GetType()) {
2209  case CTypeInfo::Type::kBool:
2210  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2211  return;
2212  case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat32:
2213  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kFloat32);
2214  return;
2215  case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat64:
2216  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
2217  return;
2218  case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt32:
2219  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2220  return;
2221  case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt64:
2222  case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint64:
2223  if (c_signature->GetInt64Representation() ==
2224  CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kBigInt) {
2225  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
2226  return;
2227  }
2228  DCHECK_EQ(c_signature->GetInt64Representation(),
2229  CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kNumber);
2230  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
2231  return;
2232  case CTypeInfo::Type::kSeqOneByteString:
2233  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2234  return;
2235  case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint32:
2236  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2237  return;
2238  case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint8:
2239  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord8);
2240  return;
2241  case CTypeInfo::Type::kAny:
2242  // This type is only supposed to be used for parameters, not returns.
2243  UNREACHABLE();
2244  case CTypeInfo::Type::kPointer:
2245  case CTypeInfo::Type::kApiObject:
2246  case CTypeInfo::Type::kV8Value:
2247  case CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid:
2248  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2249  return;
2250  }
2251  }
2252 
2253  template <Phase T>
2254  bool TryOptimizeBigInt64Shift(Node* node, const Truncation& truncation,
2255  SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
2256  DCHECK(Is64());
2257  if (!truncation.IsUsedAsWord64()) return false;
2258 
2259  Type input_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0));
2260  Type shift_amount_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
2261 
2262  if (!shift_amount_type.IsHeapConstant()) return false;
2263  HeapObjectRef ref = shift_amount_type.AsHeapConstant()->Ref();
2264  if (!ref.IsBigInt()) return false;
2265  BigIntRef bigint = ref.AsBigInt();
2266  bool lossless = false;
2267  int64_t shift_amount = bigint.AsInt64(&lossless);
2268  // We bail out if we cannot represent the shift amount correctly.
2269  if (!lossless) return false;
2270 
2271  // Canonicalize {shift_amount}.
2272  bool is_shift_left =
2273  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntShiftLeft;
2274  if (shift_amount < 0) {
2275  // A shift amount of abs(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()) is not
2276  // representable.
2277  if (shift_amount == std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()) return false;
2278  is_shift_left = !is_shift_left;
2279  shift_amount = -shift_amount;
2280  DCHECK_GT(shift_amount, 0);
2281  }
2282  DCHECK_GE(shift_amount, 0);
2283 
2284  // If the operation is a *real* left shift, propagate truncation.
2285  // If it is a *real* right shift, the output representation is
2286  // word64 only if we know the input type is BigInt64.
2287  // Otherwise, fall through to using BigIntOperationHint.
2288  if (is_shift_left) {
2289  VisitBinop<T>(node,
2290  UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
2291  UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
2292  if (lower<T>()) {
2293  if (shift_amount > 63) {
2294  DeferReplacement(node, jsgraph_->Int64Constant(0));
2295  } else if (shift_amount == 0) {
2296  DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
2297  } else {
2298  DCHECK_GE(shift_amount, 1);
2299  DCHECK_LE(shift_amount, 63);
2300  ReplaceWithPureNode(
2301  node, graph()->NewNode(lowering->machine()->Word64Shl(),
2302  node->InputAt(0),
2303  jsgraph_->Int64Constant(shift_amount)));
2304  }
2305  }
2306  return true;
2307  } else if (input_type.Is(Type::SignedBigInt64())) {
2308  VisitBinop<T>(node,
2309  UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
2310  UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
2311  if (lower<T>()) {
2312  if (shift_amount > 63) {
2313  ReplaceWithPureNode(
2314  node,
2315  graph()->NewNode(lowering->machine()->Word64Sar(),
2316  node->InputAt(0), jsgraph_->Int64Constant(63)));
2317  } else if (shift_amount == 0) {
2318  DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
2319  } else {
2320  DCHECK_GE(shift_amount, 1);
2321  DCHECK_LE(shift_amount, 63);
2322  ReplaceWithPureNode(
2323  node, graph()->NewNode(lowering->machine()->Word64Sar(),
2324  node->InputAt(0),
2325  jsgraph_->Int64Constant(shift_amount)));
2326  }
2327  }
2328  return true;
2329  } else if (input_type.Is(Type::UnsignedBigInt64())) {
2330  VisitBinop<T>(node,
2331  UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
2332  UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
2333  if (lower<T>()) {
2334  if (shift_amount > 63) {
2335  DeferReplacement(node, jsgraph_->Int64Constant(0));
2336  } else if (shift_amount == 0) {
2337  DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
2338  } else {
2339  DCHECK_GE(shift_amount, 1);
2340  DCHECK_LE(shift_amount, 63);
2341  ReplaceWithPureNode(
2342  node, graph()->NewNode(lowering->machine()->Word64Shr(),
2343  node->InputAt(0),
2344  jsgraph_->Int64Constant(shift_amount)));
2345  }
2346  }
2347  return true;
2348  }
2349 
2350  // None of the cases we can optimize here.
2351  return false;
2352  }
2353 
2354 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2355  static MachineType MachineTypeForWasmReturnType(
2356  wasm::CanonicalValueType type) {
2357  switch (type.kind()) {
2358  case wasm::kI32:
2359  return MachineType::Int32();
2360  case wasm::kI64:
2361  return MachineType::Int64();
2362  case wasm::kF32:
2363  return MachineType::Float32();
2364  case wasm::kF64:
2365  return MachineType::Float64();
2366  case wasm::kRef:
2367  case wasm::kRefNull:
2368  return MachineType::AnyTagged();
2369  default:
2370  UNREACHABLE();
2371  }
2372  }
2373 
2374  UseInfo UseInfoForJSWasmCallArgument(Node* input,
2375  wasm::CanonicalValueType type,
2376  FeedbackSource const& feedback) {
2377  // If the input type is a Number or Oddball, we can directly convert the
2378  // input into the Wasm native type of the argument. If not, we return
2379  // UseInfo::AnyTagged to signal that WasmWrapperGraphBuilder will need to
2380  // add Nodes to perform the conversion (in WasmWrapperGraphBuilder::FromJS).
2381  switch (type.kind()) {
2382  case wasm::kI32:
2383  return UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsWord32(feedback);
2384  case wasm::kI64:
2385  return UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(feedback);
2386  case wasm::kF32:
2387  case wasm::kF64:
2388  // For Float32, TruncateFloat64ToFloat32 will be inserted later in
2389  // WasmWrapperGraphBuilder::BuildJSToWasmWrapper.
2390  return UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(kDistinguishZeros,
2391  feedback);
2392  case wasm::kRef:
2393  case wasm::kRefNull:
2394  return UseInfo::AnyTagged();
2395  default:
2396  UNREACHABLE();
2397  }
2398  }
2399 
2400  template <Phase T>
2401  void VisitJSWasmCall(Node* node, SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
2402  DCHECK_EQ(JSWasmCallNode::TargetIndex(), 0);
2403  DCHECK_EQ(JSWasmCallNode::ReceiverIndex(), 1);
2404  DCHECK_EQ(JSWasmCallNode::FirstArgumentIndex(), 2);
2405 
2406  JSWasmCallNode n(node);
2407 
2408  JSWasmCallParameters const& params = n.Parameters();
2409  const wasm::CanonicalSig* wasm_signature = params.signature();
2410  int wasm_arg_count = static_cast<int>(wasm_signature->parameter_count());
2411  DCHECK_EQ(wasm_arg_count, n.ArgumentCount());
2412 
2413  base::SmallVector<UseInfo, kInitialArgumentsCount> arg_use_info(
2414  wasm_arg_count);
2415 
2416  // Visit JSFunction and Receiver nodes.
2417  ProcessInput<T>(node, JSWasmCallNode::TargetIndex(), UseInfo::Any());
2418  ProcessInput<T>(node, JSWasmCallNode::ReceiverIndex(), UseInfo::Any());
2419 
2420  // Propagate representation information from TypeInfo.
2421  for (int i = 0; i < wasm_arg_count; i++) {
2422  TNode<Object> input = n.Argument(i);
2423  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(input);
2424  arg_use_info[i] = UseInfoForJSWasmCallArgument(
2425  input, wasm_signature->GetParam(i), params.feedback());
2426  ProcessInput<T>(node, JSWasmCallNode::ArgumentIndex(i), arg_use_info[i]);
2427  }
2428 
2429  // Visit value, context and frame state inputs as tagged.
2430  int first_effect_index = NodeProperties::FirstEffectIndex(node);
2431  DCHECK(first_effect_index >
2432  JSWasmCallNode::FirstArgumentIndex() + wasm_arg_count);
2433  for (int i = JSWasmCallNode::FirstArgumentIndex() + wasm_arg_count;
2434  i < first_effect_index; i++) {
2435  ProcessInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
2436  }
2437 
2438  // Effect and Control.
2439  ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, NodeProperties::FirstEffectIndex(node));
2440 
2441  if (wasm_signature->return_count() == 1) {
2442  MachineType return_type =
2443  MachineTypeForWasmReturnType(wasm_signature->GetReturn());
2444  SetOutput<T>(
2445  node, return_type.representation(),
2446  JSWasmCallNode::TypeForWasmReturnType(wasm_signature->GetReturn()));
2447  } else {
2448  DCHECK_EQ(wasm_signature->return_count(), 0);
2449  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2450  }
2451 
2452  // The actual lowering of JSWasmCall nodes happens later, in the subsequent
2453  // "wasm-inlining" phase.
2454  }
2455 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2456 
2457  // Dispatching routine for visiting the node {node} with the usage {use}.
2458  // Depending on the operator, propagate new usage info to the inputs.
2459  template <Phase T>
2460  void VisitNode(Node* node, Truncation truncation,
2461  SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
2462  tick_counter_->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
2463 
2464  if (lower<T>()) {
2465  // Kill non-effectful operations that have a None-type input and are thus
2466  // dead code. Otherwise we might end up lowering the operation in a way,
2467  // e.g. by replacing it with a constant, that cuts the dependency on a
2468  // deopting operation (the producer of the None type), possibly resulting
2469  // in a nonsense schedule.
2470  if (node->op()->EffectOutputCount() == 0 &&
2471  node->op()->ControlOutputCount() == 0 &&
2472  node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kDeadValue &&
2473  node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kStateValues &&
2474  node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kFrameState &&
2475  node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kPhi) {
2476  for (int i = 0; i < node->op()->ValueInputCount(); i++) {
2477  Node* input = node->InputAt(i);
2478  if (TypeOf(input).IsNone()) {
2479  node->ReplaceInput(0, input);
2480  node->TrimInputCount(1);
2481  ChangeOp(node,
2482  common()->DeadValue(GetInfo(node)->representation()));
2483  return;
2484  }
2485  }
2486  } else {
2487  bool is_dead = false;
2488  if (node->op()->ValueOutputCount() > 0 &&
2489  node->op()->ControlOutputCount() == 0 &&
2490  node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kPhi &&
2491  node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kStateValues &&
2492  node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kFrameState) {
2493  for (int i = 0; i < node->op()->ValueInputCount(); i++) {
2494  Node* input = node->InputAt(i);
2495  // If one of the node's inputs produces a None-type, then this node
2496  // cannot produce a value itself.
2497  if (TypeOf(input).IsNone()) {
2498  GetInfo(node)->set_feedback_type(Type::None());
2499  is_dead = true;
2500  break;
2501  }
2502  }
2503  }
2504 
2505  InsertUnreachableIfNecessary<T>(node);
2506  // If the node is dead, we don't wont to lower it to avoid breaking
2507  // effect chains.
2508  if (is_dead) return;
2509  }
2510  }
2511 
2512  // Unconditionally eliminate unused pure nodes (only relevant if there's
2513  // a pure operation in between two effectful ones, where the last one
2514  // is unused).
2515  // Note: We must not do this for constants, as they are cached and we
2516  // would thus kill the cached {node} during lowering (i.e. replace all
2517  // uses with Dead), but at that point some node lowering might have
2518  // already taken the constant {node} from the cache (while it was not
2519  // yet killed) and we would afterwards replace that use with Dead as well.
2520  if (node->op()->ValueInputCount() > 0 &&
2521  node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kPure) && truncation.IsUnused()) {
2522  return VisitUnused<T>(node);
2523  }
2524 
2525  switch (node->opcode()) {
2526  //------------------------------------------------------------------
2527  // Common operators.
2528  //------------------------------------------------------------------
2529  case IrOpcode::kStart:
2530  // We use Start as a terminator for the frame state chain, so even
2531  // tho Start doesn't really produce a value, we have to say Tagged
2532  // here, otherwise the input conversion will fail.
2533  return VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2534  case IrOpcode::kParameter:
2535  return VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::None(),
2536  linkage()
2537  ->GetParameterType(ParameterIndexOf(node->op()))
2538  .representation());
2539  case IrOpcode::kInt32Constant:
2540  DCHECK_EQ(0, node->InputCount());
2541  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2542  DCHECK(NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Machine()));
2543  if (V8_UNLIKELY(verification_enabled())) {
2544  // During lowering, SimplifiedLowering generates Int32Constants which
2545  // need to be treated differently by the verifier than the
2546  // Int32Constants introduced explicitly in machine graphs. To be able
2547  // to distinguish them, we record those that are being visited here
2548  // because they were generated before SimplifiedLowering.
2549  if (propagate<T>()) {
2550  verifier_->RecordMachineUsesOfConstant(node, node->uses());
2551  }
2552  }
2553  return;
2554  case IrOpcode::kInt64Constant:
2555  return VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
2556  case IrOpcode::kExternalConstant:
2557  return VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
2558  case IrOpcode::kNumberConstant: {
2559  double const value = OpParameter<double>(node->op());
2560  int value_as_int;
2561  if (DoubleToSmiInteger(value, &value_as_int)) {
2562  VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned);
2563  if (lower<T>()) {
2564  intptr_t smi = base::bit_cast<intptr_t>(Smi::FromInt(value_as_int));
2565  Node* constant = InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
2566  NodeProperties::GetType(node),
2567  lowering->jsgraph()->IntPtrConstant(smi));
2568  DeferReplacement(node, constant);
2569  }
2570  return;
2571  }
2572  VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2573  return;
2574  }
2575  case IrOpcode::kHeapConstant:
2576  return VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
2577  case IrOpcode::kTrustedHeapConstant:
2578  return VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
2579  case IrOpcode::kPointerConstant: {
2580  VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
2581  if (lower<T>()) {
2582  intptr_t const value = OpParameter<intptr_t>(node->op());
2583  DeferReplacement(node, lowering->jsgraph()->IntPtrConstant(value));
2584  }
2585  return;
2586  }
2587 
2588  case IrOpcode::kBranch: {
2589  const auto& p = BranchParametersOf(node->op());
2590  if (p.semantics() == BranchSemantics::kMachine) {
2591  // If this is a machine branch, the condition is a machine operator,
2592  // so we enter machine branch here.
2593  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Any());
2594  } else {
2595  DCHECK(TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Boolean()));
2596  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Bool());
2597  if (lower<T>()) {
2598  ChangeOp(node,
2599  common()->Branch(p.hint(), BranchSemantics::kMachine));
2600  }
2601  }
2602  EnqueueInput<T>(node, NodeProperties::FirstControlIndex(node));
2603  return;
2604  }
2605  case IrOpcode::kSwitch:
2606  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
2607  EnqueueInput<T>(node, NodeProperties::FirstControlIndex(node));
2608  return;
2609  case IrOpcode::kSelect: {
2610  const auto& p = SelectParametersOf(node->op());
2611  if (p.semantics() == BranchSemantics::kMachine) {
2612  // If this is a machine select, all inputs are machine operators.
2613  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Any());
2614  ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::Any());
2615  ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::Any());
2616  SetOutput<T>(node, p.representation());
2617  } else {
2618  VisitSelect<T>(node, truncation, lowering);
2619  }
2620  return;
2621  }
2622  case IrOpcode::kPhi:
2623  return VisitPhi<T>(node, truncation, lowering);
2624  case IrOpcode::kCall:
2625  return VisitCall<T>(node, lowering);
2626  case IrOpcode::kAssert: {
2627  const auto& p = AssertParametersOf(node->op());
2628  if (p.semantics() == BranchSemantics::kMachine) {
2629  // If this is a machine condition already, we don't need to do
2630  // anything.
2631  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Any());
2632  } else {
2633  DCHECK(TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Boolean()));
2634  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Bool());
2635  if (lower<T>()) {
2636  ChangeOp(node, common()->Assert(BranchSemantics::kMachine,
2637  p.condition_string(), p.file(),
2638  p.line()));
2639  }
2640  }
2641  EnqueueInput<T>(node, NodeProperties::FirstControlIndex(node));
2642  return;
2643  }
2644 
2645  //------------------------------------------------------------------
2646  // JavaScript operators.
2647  //------------------------------------------------------------------
2648  case IrOpcode::kJSToNumber:
2649  case IrOpcode::kJSToNumberConvertBigInt:
2650  case IrOpcode::kJSToNumeric: {
2651  DCHECK(NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Union(
2652  Type::BigInt(), Type::NumberOrOddball(), graph()->zone())));
2653  VisitInputs<T>(node);
2654  // TODO(bmeurer): Optimize somewhat based on input type?
2655  if (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
2656  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2657  if (lower<T>())
2658  lowering->DoJSToNumberOrNumericTruncatesToWord32(node, this);
2659  } else if (truncation.TruncatesOddballAndBigIntToNumber()) {
2660  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
2661  if (lower<T>())
2662  lowering->DoJSToNumberOrNumericTruncatesToFloat64(node, this);
2663  } else {
2664  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2665  }
2666  return;
2667  }
2668  case IrOpcode::kJSToBigInt:
2669  case IrOpcode::kJSToBigIntConvertNumber: {
2670  VisitInputs<T>(node);
2671  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
2672  return;
2673  }
2674 
2675  //------------------------------------------------------------------
2676  // Simplified operators.
2677  //------------------------------------------------------------------
2678  case IrOpcode::kToBoolean: {
2679  if (truncation.IsUsedAsBool()) {
2680  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Bool());
2681  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2682  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
2683  } else {
2684  VisitInputs<T>(node);
2685  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
2686  }
2687  return;
2688  }
2689  case IrOpcode::kBooleanNot: {
2690  if (lower<T>()) {
2691  NodeInfo* input_info = GetInfo(node->InputAt(0));
2692  if (input_info->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kBit) {
2693  // BooleanNot(x: kRepBit) => Word32Equal(x, #0)
2694  node->AppendInput(jsgraph_->zone(), jsgraph_->Int32Constant(0));
2695  ChangeOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Equal());
2696  } else if (CanBeTaggedPointer(input_info->representation())) {
2697  // BooleanNot(x: kRepTagged) => TaggedEqual(x, #false)
2698  node->AppendInput(jsgraph_->zone(), jsgraph_->FalseConstant());
2699  ChangeOp(node, lowering->machine()->TaggedEqual());
2700  } else {
2701  DCHECK(TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).IsNone());
2702  DeferReplacement(node, lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0));
2703  }
2704  } else {
2705  // No input representation requirement; adapt during lowering.
2706  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTruncatingToBool());
2707  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2708  }
2709  return;
2710  }
2711  case IrOpcode::kNumberEqual: {
2712  Type const lhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
2713  Type const rhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
2714  // Regular number comparisons in JavaScript generally identify zeros,
2715  // so we always pass kIdentifyZeros for the inputs, and in addition
2716  // we can truncate -0 to 0 for otherwise Unsigned32 or Signed32 inputs.
2717  // For equality we also handle the case that one side is non-zero, in
2718  // which case we allow to truncate NaN to 0 on the other side.
2719  if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()) &&
2720  rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero())) ||
2721  (lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
2722  rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
2723  OneInputCannotBe(node, type_cache_->kZeroish))) {
2724  // => unsigned Int32Cmp
2725  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2726  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2727  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Uint32Op(node));
2728  return;
2729  }
2730  if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
2731  rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero())) ||
2732  (lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
2733  rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
2734  OneInputCannotBe(node, type_cache_->kZeroish))) {
2735  // => signed Int32Cmp
2736  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2737  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2738  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2739  return;
2740  }
2741  if (lhs_type.Is(Type::Boolean()) && rhs_type.Is(Type::Boolean())) {
2742  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::Bool(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2743  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Equal());
2744  return;
2745  }
2746  // => Float64Cmp
2747  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(kIdentifyZeros),
2748  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2749  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2750  return;
2751  }
2752  case IrOpcode::kNumberLessThan:
2753  case IrOpcode::kNumberLessThanOrEqual: {
2754  Type const lhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
2755  Type const rhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
2756  // Regular number comparisons in JavaScript generally identify zeros,
2757  // so we always pass kIdentifyZeros for the inputs, and in addition
2758  // we can truncate -0 to 0 for otherwise Unsigned32 or Signed32 inputs.
2759  if (lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()) &&
2760  rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero())) {
2761  // => unsigned Int32Cmp
2762  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2763  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2764  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Uint32Op(node));
2765  } else if (lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
2766  rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero())) {
2767  // => signed Int32Cmp
2768  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2769  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2770  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2771  } else {
2772  // => Float64Cmp
2773  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(kIdentifyZeros),
2774  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2775  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2776  }
2777  return;
2778  }
2779 
2780  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeSmallIntegerAdd:
2781  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeSmallIntegerSubtract:
2782  return VisitSpeculativeSmallIntegerAdditiveOp<T>(node, truncation,
2783  lowering);
2784 
2785  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeAdditiveSafeIntegerAdd:
2786  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeAdditiveSafeIntegerSubtract:
2787  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberAdd:
2788  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberSubtract:
2789  return VisitSpeculativeAdditiveOp<T>(node, truncation, lowering);
2790 
2791  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberLessThan:
2792  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberLessThanOrEqual:
2793  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberEqual: {
2794  Type const lhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
2795  Type const rhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
2796  // Regular number comparisons in JavaScript generally identify zeros,
2797  // so we always pass kIdentifyZeros for the inputs, and in addition
2798  // we can truncate -0 to 0 for otherwise Unsigned32 or Signed32 inputs.
2799  if (lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()) &&
2800  rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero())) {
2801  // => unsigned Int32Cmp
2802  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2803  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2804  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Uint32Op(node));
2805  return;
2806  } else if (lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
2807  rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero())) {
2808  // => signed Int32Cmp
2809  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2810  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2811  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2812  return;
2813  } else if (lhs_type.Is(Type::Boolean()) &&
2814  rhs_type.Is(Type::Boolean())) {
2815  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::Bool(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2816  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2817  return;
2818  }
2819  // Try to use type feedback.
2820  NumberOperationHint hint = NumberOperationHintOf(node->op());
2821  switch (hint) {
2822  case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
2823  if (propagate<T>()) {
2824  VisitBinop<T>(
2825  node, CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros),
2826  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2827  } else if (retype<T>()) {
2828  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kBit, Type::Any());
2829  } else {
2830  DCHECK(lower<T>());
2831  Node* lhs = node->InputAt(0);
2832  Node* rhs = node->InputAt(1);
2833  if (IsNodeRepresentationTagged(lhs) &&
2834  IsNodeRepresentationTagged(rhs)) {
2835  VisitBinop<T>(node,
2836  UseInfo::CheckedSignedSmallAsTaggedSigned(
2837  FeedbackSource(), kIdentifyZeros),
2838  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2839  ChangeToPureOp(
2840  node, changer_->TaggedSignedOperatorFor(node->opcode()));
2841 
2842  } else {
2843  VisitBinop<T>(
2844  node, CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros),
2845  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2846  ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2847  }
2848  }
2849  return;
2850  case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs:
2851  case NumberOperationHint::kAdditiveSafeInteger:
2852  // This doesn't make sense for compare operations.
2853  UNREACHABLE();
2854  case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball:
2855  // Abstract and strict equality don't perform ToNumber conversions
2856  // on Oddballs, so make sure we don't accidentially sneak in a
2857  // hint with Oddball feedback here.
2858  DCHECK_NE(IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberEqual, node->opcode());
2859  [[fallthrough]];
2860  case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrBoolean:
2861  case NumberOperationHint::kNumber:
2862  VisitBinop<T>(node,
2863  CheckedUseInfoAsFloat64FromHint(
2864  hint, FeedbackSource(), kIdentifyZeros),
2865  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2866  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2867  return;
2868  }
2869  UNREACHABLE();
2870  return;
2871  }
2872 
2873  case IrOpcode::kNumberAdd:
2874  case IrOpcode::kNumberSubtract: {
2875  if (TypeOf(node->InputAt(0))
2876  .Is(type_cache_->kAdditiveSafeIntegerOrMinusZero) &&
2877  TypeOf(node->InputAt(1))
2878  .Is(type_cache_->kAdditiveSafeIntegerOrMinusZero) &&
2879  (TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Signed32()) ||
2880  TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) ||
2881  truncation.IsUsedAsWord32())) {
2882  // => Int32Add/Sub
2883  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2884  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2885  } else if (jsgraph_->machine()->Is64() &&
2886  BothInputsAre(node, type_cache_->kSafeInteger) &&
2887  GetUpperBound(node).Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger)) {
2888  // => Int64Add/Sub
2889  VisitInt64Binop<T>(node);
2890  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int64Op(node));
2891  } else {
2892  // => Float64Add/Sub
2893  VisitFloat64Binop<T>(node);
2894  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2895  }
2896  return;
2897  }
2898  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberMultiply: {
2899  if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::Integral32()) &&
2900  (NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Signed32()) ||
2901  NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) ||
2902  (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() &&
2903  NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(
2904  type_cache_->kSafeIntegerOrMinusZero)))) {
2905  // Multiply reduces to Int32Mul if the inputs are integers, and
2906  // (a) the output is either known to be Signed32, or
2907  // (b) the output is known to be Unsigned32, or
2908  // (c) the uses are truncating and the result is in the safe
2909  // integer range.
2910  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2911  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2912  return;
2913  }
2914  // Try to use type feedback.
2915  NumberOperationHint hint = NumberOperationHintOf(node->op());
2916  Type input0_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
2917  Type input1_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
2918 
2919  // Handle the case when no int32 checks on inputs are necessary
2920  // (but an overflow check is needed on the output).
2921  if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::Signed32())) {
2922  // If both inputs and feedback are int32, use the overflow op.
2923  if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
2924  VisitForCheckedInt32Mul<T>(node, truncation, input0_type,
2925  input1_type,
2926  UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
2927  return;
2928  }
2929  }
2930 
2931  if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
2932  VisitForCheckedInt32Mul<T>(node, truncation, input0_type, input1_type,
2933  CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint));
2934  return;
2935  }
2936 
2937  // Checked float64 x float64 => float64
2938  VisitBinop<T>(node,
2939  UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(
2940  kDistinguishZeros, FeedbackSource()),
2941  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, Type::Number());
2942  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2943  return;
2944  }
2945  case IrOpcode::kNumberMultiply: {
2946  if (TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Integral32()) &&
2947  TypeOf(node->InputAt(1)).Is(Type::Integral32()) &&
2948  (TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Signed32()) ||
2949  TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) ||
2950  (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() &&
2951  TypeOf(node).Is(type_cache_->kSafeIntegerOrMinusZero)))) {
2952  // Multiply reduces to Int32Mul if the inputs are integers, and
2953  // (a) the output is either known to be Signed32, or
2954  // (b) the output is known to be Unsigned32, or
2955  // (c) the uses are truncating and the result is in the safe
2956  // integer range.
2957  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2958  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2959  return;
2960  }
2961  // Number x Number => Float64Mul
2962  VisitFloat64Binop<T>(node);
2963  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2964  return;
2965  }
2966  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberDivide: {
2967  if (BothInputsAreUnsigned32(node) && truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
2968  // => unsigned Uint32Div
2969  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2970  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Uint32Div(node));
2971  return;
2972  }
2973  if (BothInputsAreSigned32(node)) {
2974  if (NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Signed32())) {
2975  // => signed Int32Div
2976  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2977  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Div(node));
2978  return;
2979  }
2980  if (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
2981  // => signed Int32Div
2982  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2983  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Div(node));
2984  return;
2985  }
2986  }
2987 
2988  // Try to use type feedback.
2989  NumberOperationHint hint = NumberOperationHintOf(node->op());
2990 
2991  // Handle the case when no uint32 checks on inputs are necessary
2992  // (but an overflow check is needed on the output).
2993  if (BothInputsAreUnsigned32(node)) {
2994  if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
2995  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2996  MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Unsigned32());
2997  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToUint32OverflowOp(node);
2998  return;
2999  }
3000  }
3001 
3002  // Handle the case when no int32 checks on inputs are necessary
3003  // (but an overflow check is needed on the output).
3004  if (BothInputsAreSigned32(node)) {
3005  // If both the inputs the feedback are int32, use the overflow op.
3006  if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
3007  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3008  MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Signed32());
3009  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToInt32OverflowOp(node);
3010  return;
3011  }
3012  }
3013 
3014  if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall ||
3015  hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs) {
3016  // If the result is truncated, we only need to check the inputs.
3017  if (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
3018  VisitBinop<T>(node, CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint),
3019  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3020  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Div(node));
3021  return;
3022  } else if (hint != NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs) {
3023  VisitBinop<T>(node, CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint),
3024  MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Signed32());
3025  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToInt32OverflowOp(node);
3026  return;
3027  }
3028  }
3029 
3030  // default case => Float64Div
3031  VisitBinop<T>(node,
3032  UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(
3033  kDistinguishZeros, FeedbackSource()),
3034  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, Type::Number());
3035  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3036  return;
3037  }
3038  case IrOpcode::kNumberDivide: {
3039  if (TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) &&
3040  TypeOf(node->InputAt(1)).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) &&
3041  (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
3042  TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()))) {
3043  // => unsigned Uint32Div
3044  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
3045  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Uint32Div(node));
3046  return;
3047  }
3048  if (TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Signed32()) &&
3049  TypeOf(node->InputAt(1)).Is(Type::Signed32()) &&
3050  (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
3051  TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Signed32()))) {
3052  // => signed Int32Div
3053  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
3054  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Div(node));
3055  return;

3059  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3060  return;
3061  }

3063  CHECK(TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Unsigned32()));

3066  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
3067  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Uint32Div(node));
3068  return;
3069  }
3070  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberModulus:
3071  return VisitSpeculativeNumberModulus<T>(node, truncation, lowering);
3072  case IrOpcode::kNumberModulus: {
3073  Type const lhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3074  Type const rhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
3075  if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
3076  rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZeroOrNaN())) &&
3077  (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
3078  TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()))) {
3079  // => unsigned Uint32Mod
3080  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
3081  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Uint32Mod(node));
3082  return;
3083  }

3085  rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZeroOrNaN())) &&
3086  (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() || TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Signed32()) ||
3087  (truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero() &&
3088  TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero())))) {
3089  // => signed Int32Mod
3090  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
3091  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Mod(node));
3092  return;
3093  }
3094  // => Float64Mod
3095  // For the left hand side we just propagate the identify zeros
3096  // mode of the {truncation}; and for modulus the sign of the
3097  // right hand side doesn't matter anyways, so in particular there's
3098  // no observable difference between a 0 and a -0 then.
3099  UseInfo const lhs_use =
3100  UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(truncation.identify_zeros());
3101  UseInfo const rhs_use = UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(kIdentifyZeros);
3102  VisitBinop<T>(node, lhs_use, rhs_use, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3103  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3104  return;
3105  }
3106  case IrOpcode::kNumberBitwiseOr:
3107  case IrOpcode::kNumberBitwiseXor:
3108  case IrOpcode::kNumberBitwiseAnd: {
3109  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
3110  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Int32Op(node));
3111  return;
3112  }
3113  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberBitwiseOr:
3114  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberBitwiseXor:
3115  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberBitwiseAnd:

3117  if (lower<T>()) {
3118  ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
3119  }
3120  return;
3121  case IrOpcode::kNumberShiftLeft: {
3122  Type rhs_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
3123  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3124  UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3125  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3126  if (lower<T>()) {
3127  MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
3128  ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Shl());
3129  }
3130  return;
3131  }

3136  UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3137  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3138  if (lower<T>()) {
3139  MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
3140  ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Shl());
3141  }
3142  return;
3143  }

3145  Type rhs_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));

3147  CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros),
3148  MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Signed32());
3149  if (lower<T>()) {
3150  MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
3151  ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Shl());
3152  }
3153  return;
3154  }

3156  Type rhs_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
3157  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3158  UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3159  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3160  if (lower<T>()) {
3161  MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
3162  ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Sar());

3167  if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::NumberOrOddball())) {
3168  Type rhs_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
3169  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),

3180  VisitBinop<T>(node,
3181  CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros),
3182  MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Signed32());
3183  if (lower<T>()) {
3184  MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
3185  ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Sar());
3186  }

3190  Type rhs_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
3191  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3192  UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3193  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3194  if (lower<T>()) {
3195  MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);

3200  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberShiftRightLogical: {
3201  NumberOperationHint hint = NumberOperationHintOf(node->op());
3202  Type rhs_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
3203  if (rhs_type.Is(type_cache_->kZeroish) &&
3204  hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall &&
3205  !truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
3206  // The SignedSmall or Signed32 feedback means that the results that we
3207  // have seen so far were of type Unsigned31. We speculate that this
3208  // will continue to hold. Moreover, since the RHS is 0, the result
3209  // will just be the (converted) LHS.
3210  VisitBinop<T>(node,
3211  CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros),
3212  MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Unsigned31());
3213  if (lower<T>()) {
3214  node->RemoveInput(1);
3215  ChangeOp(node,
3216  simplified()->CheckedUint32ToInt32(FeedbackSource()));
3217  }
3218  return;
3219  }

3221  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3222  UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3223  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3224  if (lower<T>()) {
3225  MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
3226  ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Shr());
3227  }
3228  return;
3229  }
3230  VisitBinop<T>(node,
3231  CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros),
3232  MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Unsigned32());
3233  if (lower<T>()) {
3234  MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
3235  ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Shr());
3236  }
3237  return;
3238  }
3239  case IrOpcode::kNumberAbs: {
3240  // NumberAbs maps both 0 and -0 to 0, so we can generally
3241  // pass the kIdentifyZeros truncation to its input, and
3242  // choose to ignore minus zero in all cases.
3243  Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3244  if (input_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero())) {
3245  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3246  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3247  if (lower<T>()) {
3248  DeferReplacement(
3249  node,
3250  InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
3251  Type::Intersect(input_type, Type::Unsigned32(), zone()),
3252  node->InputAt(0)));
3253  }
3254  } else if (input_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero())) {
3255  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3256  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3257  if (lower<T>()) {
3258  DeferReplacement(
3259  node,
3260  InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
3261  Type::Intersect(input_type, Type::Unsigned32(), zone()),
3262  lowering->Int32Abs(node)));
3263  }

3265  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(kIdentifyZeros),
3266  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3267  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
3268  } else {

3270  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);

3272  }

3274  }

3279  return;
3280  }

3285  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Uint32Op(node));
