3291  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3292  return;
3293  }
3294  case IrOpcode::kNumberMax: {
3295  // It is safe to use the feedback types for left and right hand side
3296  // here, since we can only narrow those types and thus we can only
3297  // promise a more specific truncation.
3298  // For NumberMax we generally propagate whether the truncation
3299  // identifies zeros to the inputs, and we choose to ignore minus
3300  // zero in those cases.
3301  Type const lhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3302  Type const rhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
3303  if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32()) &&
3304  rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32())) ||
3305  (lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()) &&
3306  rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()) &&
3307  truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero())) {
3308  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
3309  if (lower<T>()) {
3310  lowering->DoMax(node, lowering->machine()->Uint32LessThan(),
3311  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3312  }
3313  } else if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32()) &&
3314  rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32())) ||
3315  (lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
3316  rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
3317  truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero())) {
3318  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
3319  if (lower<T>()) {
3320  lowering->DoMax(node, lowering->machine()->Int32LessThan(),
3321  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3322  }
3323  } else if (jsgraph_->machine()->Is64() &&
3324  lhs_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger) &&
3325  rhs_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger)) {
3326  VisitInt64Binop<T>(node);
3327  if (lower<T>()) {
3328  lowering->DoMax(node, lowering->machine()->Int64LessThan(),
3329  MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
3330  }
3331  } else {
3332  VisitBinop<T>(node,
3333  UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(truncation.identify_zeros()),
3334  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3335  if (lower<T>()) {
3336  // If the right hand side is not NaN, and the left hand side
3337  // is not NaN (or -0 if the difference between the zeros is
3338  // observed), we can do a simple floating point comparison here.
3339  if (lhs_type.Is(truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero()
3340  ? Type::OrderedNumber()
3341  : Type::PlainNumber()) &&
3342  rhs_type.Is(Type::OrderedNumber())) {
3343  lowering->DoMax(node, lowering->machine()->Float64LessThan(),
3344  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3345  } else {
3346  ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3347  }
3348  }
3349  }
3350  return;
3351  }
3352  case IrOpcode::kNumberMin: {
3353  // It is safe to use the feedback types for left and right hand side
3354  // here, since we can only narrow those types and thus we can only
3355  // promise a more specific truncation.
3356  // For NumberMin we generally propagate whether the truncation
3357  // identifies zeros to the inputs, and we choose to ignore minus
3358  // zero in those cases.
3359  Type const lhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3360  Type const rhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
3361  if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32()) &&
3362  rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32())) ||
3363  (lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()) &&
3364  rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()) &&
3365  truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero())) {
3366  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
3367  if (lower<T>()) {
3368  lowering->DoMin(node, lowering->machine()->Uint32LessThan(),
3369  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3370  }
3371  } else if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32()) &&
3372  rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32())) ||
3373  (lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
3374  rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
3375  truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero())) {
3376  VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
3377  if (lower<T>()) {
3378  lowering->DoMin(node, lowering->machine()->Int32LessThan(),
3379  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3380  }
3381  } else if (jsgraph_->machine()->Is64() &&
3382  lhs_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger) &&
3383  rhs_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger)) {
3384  VisitInt64Binop<T>(node);
3385  if (lower<T>()) {
3386  lowering->DoMin(node, lowering->machine()->Int64LessThan(),
3387  MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
3388  }
3389  } else {
3390  VisitBinop<T>(node,
3391  UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(truncation.identify_zeros()),
3392  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3393  if (lower<T>()) {
3394  // If the left hand side is not NaN, and the right hand side
3395  // is not NaN (or -0 if the difference between the zeros is
3396  // observed), we can do a simple floating point comparison here.
3397  if (lhs_type.Is(Type::OrderedNumber()) &&
3398  rhs_type.Is(truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero()
3399  ? Type::OrderedNumber()
3400  : Type::PlainNumber())) {
3401  lowering->DoMin(node,
3402  lowering->machine()->Float64LessThanOrEqual(),
3403  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3404  } else {
3405  ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3406  }
3407  }
3408  }
3409  return;
3410  }
3411  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberPow: {
3412  // Checked float64 ** float64 => float64
3413  VisitBinop<T>(node,
3414  UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(
3415  kDistinguishZeros, FeedbackSource()),
3416  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, Type::Number());
3417  if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3418  return;
3419  }
3420  case IrOpcode::kNumberAtan2:
3421  case IrOpcode::kNumberPow: {
3422  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
3423  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3424  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3425  return;
3426  }
3427  case IrOpcode::kNumberCeil:
3428  case IrOpcode::kNumberFloor:
3429  case IrOpcode::kNumberRound:
3430  case IrOpcode::kNumberTrunc: {
3431  // For NumberCeil, NumberFloor, NumberRound and NumberTrunc we propagate
3432  // the zero identification part of the truncation, and we turn them into
3433  // no-ops if we figure out (late) that their input is already an
3434  // integer, NaN or -0.
3435  Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3436  VisitUnop<T>(node,
3437  UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(truncation.identify_zeros()),
3438  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3439  if (lower<T>()) {
3440  if (input_type.Is(type_cache_->kIntegerOrMinusZeroOrNaN)) {
3441  DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
3442  } else if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kNumberRound) {
3443  DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Float64Round(node));
3444  } else {
3445  ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3446  }
3447  }
3448  return;
3449  }
3450  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntAsIntN:
3451  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntAsUintN: {
3452  const bool is_asuintn =
3453  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntAsUintN;
3454  const auto p = SpeculativeBigIntAsNParametersOf(node->op());
3455  DCHECK_LE(0, p.bits());
3456  DCHECK_LE(p.bits(), 64);
3457 
3458  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0,
3459  UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(p.feedback()));
3460  SetOutput<T>(
3461  node, MachineRepresentation::kWord64,
3462  is_asuintn ? Type::UnsignedBigInt64() : Type::SignedBigInt64());
3463  if (lower<T>()) {
3464  if (p.bits() == 0) {
3465  DeferReplacement(node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
3466  Type::UnsignedBigInt63(),
3467  jsgraph_->Int64Constant(0)));
3468  } else if (p.bits() == 64) {
3469  DeferReplacement(node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
3470  is_asuintn ? Type::UnsignedBigInt64()
3471  : Type::SignedBigInt64(),
3472  node->InputAt(0)));
3473  } else {
3474  if (is_asuintn) {
3475  const uint64_t mask = (1ULL << p.bits()) - 1ULL;
3476  ChangeUnaryToPureBinaryOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word64And(),
3477  1, jsgraph_->Int64Constant(mask));
3478  } else {
3479  // We truncate the value to N bits, but to correctly interpret
3480  // negative values, we have to fill the top (64-N) bits with the
3481  // sign. This is done by shifting the value left and then back
3482  // with an arithmetic right shift. E.g. for {value} =
3483  // 0..0'0001'1101 (29n) and N = 3: {shifted} is 1010'0000'0..0
3484  // after left shift by 61 bits, {unshifted} is 1..1'1111'1101
3485  // after arithmetic right shift by 61. This is the 64 bit
3486  // representation of -3 we expect for the signed 3 bit integer
3487  // 101.
3488  const uint64_t shift = 64 - p.bits();
3489  Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
3490  Node* shifted =
3491  graph()->NewNode(lowering->machine()->Word64Shl(), value,
3492  jsgraph_->Uint64Constant(shift));
3493  Node* unshifted =
3494  graph()->NewNode(lowering->machine()->Word64Sar(), shifted,
3495  jsgraph_->Uint64Constant(shift));
3496 
3497  ReplaceWithPureNode(node, unshifted);
3498  }
3499  }
3500  }
3501  return;
3502  }
3503  case IrOpcode::kNumberAcos:
3504  case IrOpcode::kNumberAcosh:
3505  case IrOpcode::kNumberAsin:
3506  case IrOpcode::kNumberAsinh:
3507  case IrOpcode::kNumberAtan:
3508  case IrOpcode::kNumberAtanh:
3509  case IrOpcode::kNumberCos:
3510  case IrOpcode::kNumberCosh:
3511  case IrOpcode::kNumberExp:
3512  case IrOpcode::kNumberExpm1:
3513  case IrOpcode::kNumberLog:
3514  case IrOpcode::kNumberLog1p:
3515  case IrOpcode::kNumberLog2:
3516  case IrOpcode::kNumberLog10:
3517  case IrOpcode::kNumberCbrt:
3518  case IrOpcode::kNumberSin:
3519  case IrOpcode::kNumberSinh:
3520  case IrOpcode::kNumberTan:
3521  case IrOpcode::kNumberTanh: {
3522  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
3523  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3524  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3525  return;
3526  }
3527  case IrOpcode::kNumberSign: {
3528  if (InputIs(node, Type::Signed32())) {
3529  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3530  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3531  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Sign(node));
3532  } else {
3533  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
3534  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3535  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Float64Sign(node));
3536  }
3537  return;
3538  }
3539  case IrOpcode::kNumberSilenceNaN: {
3540  Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3541  if (input_type.Is(Type::OrderedNumber())) {
3542  // No need to silence anything if the input cannot be NaN.
3543  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
3544  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3545  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
3546  } else {
3547  SilenceNanMode mode = SilenceNanModeOf(node->op());
3548  if (mode == SilenceNanMode::kPreserveUndefined &&
3549  input_type.Maybe(Type::Undefined())) {
3550  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64OrUndefined(),
3551  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3552  // We preserve NumberSilenceNaN here and lower in graph builder.
3553  } else {
3554  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
3555  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3556  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3557  }
3558  }
3559  return;
3560  }
3561  case IrOpcode::kNumberSqrt: {
3562  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
3563  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3564  if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3565  return;
3566  }
3567  case IrOpcode::kNumberToBoolean: {
3568  // For NumberToBoolean we don't care whether the input is 0 or
3569  // -0, since both of them are mapped to false anyways, so we
3570  // can generally pass kIdentifyZeros truncation.
3571  Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3572  if (input_type.Is(Type::Integral32OrMinusZeroOrNaN())) {
3573  // 0, -0 and NaN all map to false, so we can safely truncate
3574  // all of them to zero here.
3575  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3576  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
3577  if (lower<T>()) lowering->DoIntegral32ToBit(node);
3578  } else if (input_type.Is(Type::OrderedNumber())) {
3579  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(kIdentifyZeros),
3580  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
3581  if (lower<T>()) lowering->DoOrderedNumberToBit(node);
3582  } else {
3583  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(kIdentifyZeros),
3584  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
3585  if (lower<T>()) lowering->DoNumberToBit(node);
3586  }
3587  return;
3588  }
3589  case IrOpcode::kNumberToInt32: {
3590  // Just change representation if necessary.
3591  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3592  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3593  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
3594  return;
3595  }
3596  case IrOpcode::kNumberToString: {
3597  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
3598  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3599  return;
3600  }
3601  case IrOpcode::kNumberToUint32: {
3602  // Just change representation if necessary.
3603  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3604  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3605  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
3606  return;
3607  }
3608  case IrOpcode::kNumberToUint8Clamped: {
3609  Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3610  if (input_type.Is(type_cache_->kUint8OrMinusZeroOrNaN)) {
3611  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3612  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3613  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
3614  } else if (input_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZeroOrNaN())) {
3615  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3616  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3617  if (lower<T>()) lowering->DoUnsigned32ToUint8Clamped(node);
3618  } else if (input_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZeroOrNaN())) {
3619  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3620  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3621  if (lower<T>()) lowering->DoSigned32ToUint8Clamped(node);
3622  } else if (input_type.Is(type_cache_->kIntegerOrMinusZeroOrNaN)) {
3623  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
3624  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3625  if (lower<T>()) lowering->DoIntegerToUint8Clamped(node);
3626  } else {
3627  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
3628  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3629  if (lower<T>()) lowering->DoNumberToUint8Clamped(node);
3630  }
3631  return;
3632  }
3633  case IrOpcode::kIntegral32OrMinusZeroToBigInt: {
3634  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Word64(kIdentifyZeros),
3635  MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
3636  if (lower<T>()) {
3637  DeferReplacement(
3638  node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(NodeProperties::GetType(node),
3639  node->InputAt(0)));
3640  }
3641  return;
3642  }
3643  case IrOpcode::kReferenceEqual: {
3644  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
3645  if (lower<T>()) {
3646  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
3647  ChangeOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Equal());
3648  } else {
3649  ChangeOp(node, lowering->machine()->WordEqual());
3650  }
3651  }
3652  return;
3653  }
3654  case IrOpcode::kSameValueNumbersOnly: {
3655  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
3656  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3657  return;
3658  }
3659  case IrOpcode::kSameValue: {
3660  if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
3661  if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::Number())) {
3662  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
3663  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
3664  if (lower<T>()) {
3665  ChangeOp(node, lowering->simplified()->NumberSameValue());
3666  }
3667  } else {
3668  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
3669  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3670  }
3671  return;
3672  }
3673  case IrOpcode::kTypeOf: {
3674  return VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
3675  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3676  }
3677  case IrOpcode::kNewConsString: {
3678  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32()); // length
3679  ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // first
3680  ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // second
3681  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3682  return;
3683  }
3684  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntAdd:
3685  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntSubtract:
3686  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntMultiply: {
3687  if (truncation.IsUnused() && BothInputsAre(node, Type::BigInt())) {
3688  VisitUnused<T>(node);
3689  return;
3690  }
3691  if (Is64() && truncation.IsUsedAsWord64()) {
3692  VisitBinop<T>(
3693  node, UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
3694  MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
3695  if (lower<T>()) {
3696  ChangeToPureOp(node, Int64Op(node));
3697  }
3698  return;
3699  }
3700  BigIntOperationHint hint = BigIntOperationHintOf(node->op());
3701  switch (hint) {
3702  case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt64: {
3703  VisitBinop<T>(
3704  node, UseInfo::CheckedBigInt64AsWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
3705  MachineRepresentation::kWord64, Type::SignedBigInt64());
3706  if (lower<T>()) {
3707  ChangeOp(node, Int64OverflowOp(node));
3708  }
3709  return;
3710  }
3711  case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt: {
3712  VisitBinop<T>(
3713  node, UseInfo::CheckedBigIntAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource{}),
3714  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3715  if (lower<T>()) {
3716  ChangeOp(node, BigIntOp(node));
3717  }
3718  return;
3719  }
3720  }
3721  }
3722  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntDivide:
3723  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntModulus: {
3724  if (truncation.IsUnused() && BothInputsAre(node, Type::BigInt())) {
3725  VisitUnused<T>(node);
3726  return;
3727  }
3728  BigIntOperationHint hint = BigIntOperationHintOf(node->op());
3729  switch (hint) {
3730  case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt64: {
3731  VisitBinop<T>(
3732  node, UseInfo::CheckedBigInt64AsWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
3733  MachineRepresentation::kWord64, Type::SignedBigInt64());
3734  if (lower<T>()) {
3735  ChangeOp(node, Int64OverflowOp(node));
3736  }
3737  return;
3738  }
3739  case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt: {
3740  VisitBinop<T>(
3741  node, UseInfo::CheckedBigIntAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource{}),
3742  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3743  if (lower<T>()) {
3744  ChangeOp(node, BigIntOp(node));
3745  }
3746  return;
3747  }
3748  }
3749  }
3750  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntBitwiseAnd:
3751  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntBitwiseOr:
3752  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntBitwiseXor: {
3753  if (truncation.IsUnused() && BothInputsAre(node, Type::BigInt())) {
3754  VisitUnused<T>(node);
3755  return;
3756  }
3757  if (Is64() && truncation.IsUsedAsWord64()) {
3758  VisitBinop<T>(
3759  node, UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
3760  MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
3761  if (lower<T>()) {
3762  ChangeToPureOp(node, Int64Op(node));
3763  }
3764  return;
3765  }
3766  BigIntOperationHint hint = BigIntOperationHintOf(node->op());
3767  switch (hint) {
3768  case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt64: {
3769  VisitBinop<T>(
3770  node, UseInfo::CheckedBigInt64AsWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
3771  MachineRepresentation::kWord64, Type::SignedBigInt64());
3772  if (lower<T>()) {
3773  ChangeToPureOp(node, Int64Op(node));
3774  }
3775  return;

3778  VisitBinop<T>(
3779  node, UseInfo::CheckedBigIntAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource{}),

3784  return;
3785  }

3789  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntShiftRight: {

3800  UseInfo::CheckedBigIntAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource{}),

3806  }
3807  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntEqual:
3808  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntLessThan:
3809  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntLessThanOrEqual: {

3811  // operand to primitive.

3830  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3831  if (lower<T>()) {
3832  ChangeToPureOp(node, BigIntOp(node));
3833  }
3834  return;
3835  }
3836  }
3837  }
3838  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntNegate: {
3839  // NOTE: If truncation is Unused, we still need to preserve at least the
3840  // BigInt type check (see http://crbug.com/1431713 for some details).
3841  // We can use the standard lowering to word64 operations and have
3842  // following phases remove the unused truncation and subtraction
3843  // operations.

3861  }
3862  case IrOpcode::kStringConcat: {
3863  // TODO(turbofan): We currently depend on having this first length input

3875  case IrOpcode::kStringLessThan:

3923  }
3924  case IrOpcode::kStringSubstring: {
3925  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged());

3930  return;

3933  case IrOpcode::kStringToUpperCaseIntl: {

3935  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3936  return;
3937  }
3938  case IrOpcode::kCheckBounds:
3939  return VisitCheckBounds<T>(node, lowering);
3940  case IrOpcode::kCheckHeapObject: {

3943  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);

3947  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);

3950  return;
3951  }

3956  return;
3957  }

3960  return;
3961  }

3966  } else {

3968  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
3969  }
3970  return;
3971  }

3973  Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));

3975  Type::Intersect(input_type, Type::NumberOrUndefined(), zone());

3978  VisitUnused<T>(node);
3979  } else if (truncation.TruncatesBooleanAndNullAndBigIntToNumber()) {
3980  VisitUnop<T>(node,

3982  truncation.identify_zeros()),
3983  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, output_type);
3984  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
3985  } else {
3986  VisitNoop<T>(node, truncation);
3987  }
3988  } else {
3989  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
3990  MachineRepresentation::kTagged, output_type);
3991  }
3992  return;
3993  }
3994  case IrOpcode::kCheckNumberFitsInt32: {
3995  Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3996  if (input_type.Is(Type::Signed32())) {
3997  VisitNoop<T>(node, truncation);
3998  } else {
3999  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4000  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4001  }

4003  }

4006  return;

4110  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);

4113  case IrOpcode::kLoadField: {

4115  FieldAccess access = FieldAccessOf(node->op());
4116  MachineRepresentation const representation =
4117  access.machine_type.representation();
4118  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfoForBasePointer(access), representation);
4119  return;
4120  }
4121  case IrOpcode::kStoreField: {
4122  FieldAccess access = FieldAccessOf(node->op());
4123  Node* value_node = node->InputAt(1);
4124  NodeInfo* input_info = GetInfo(value_node);
4125  MachineRepresentation field_representation =
4126  access.machine_type.representation();
4127 
4128  // Convert to Smi if possible, such that we can avoid a write barrier.
4129  if (field_representation == MachineRepresentation::kTagged &&
4130  TypeOf(value_node).Is(Type::SignedSmall())) {
4131  field_representation = MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned;
4132  }
4133  WriteBarrierKind write_barrier_kind = WriteBarrierKindFor(
4134  access.base_is_tagged, field_representation, access.offset,
4135  access.type, input_info->representation(), value_node);
4136 
4137  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfoForBasePointer(access));
4138  ProcessInput<T>(
4139  node, 1, TruncatingUseInfoFromRepresentation(field_representation));
4140  ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 2);
4141  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4142  if (lower<T>()) {
4143  if (write_barrier_kind < access.write_barrier_kind) {
4144  access.write_barrier_kind = write_barrier_kind;
4145  ChangeOp(node, jsgraph_->simplified()->StoreField(access));
4146  }
4147  }
4148  return;
4149  }
4150  case IrOpcode::kLoadElement: {
4151  if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
4152  ElementAccess access = ElementAccessOf(node->op());
4153  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfoForBasePointer(access), UseInfo::Word(),
4154  access.machine_type.representation());
4155  return;
4156  }
4157  case IrOpcode::kLoadStackArgument: {
4158  if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
4159  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::Word(), MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4160  return;
4161  }
4162  case IrOpcode::kStoreElement: {
4163  ElementAccess access = ElementAccessOf(node->op());
4164  Node* value_node = node->InputAt(2);
4165  NodeInfo* input_info = GetInfo(value_node);
4166  MachineRepresentation element_representation =
4167  access.machine_type.representation();
4168 
4169  // Convert to Smi if possible, such that we can avoid a write barrier.
4170  if (element_representation == MachineRepresentation::kTagged &&
4171  TypeOf(value_node).Is(Type::SignedSmall())) {
4172  element_representation = MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned;
4173  }
4174  WriteBarrierKind write_barrier_kind = WriteBarrierKindFor(
4175  access.base_is_tagged, element_representation, access.type,
4176  input_info->representation(), value_node);
4177  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfoForBasePointer(access)); // base
4178  ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::Word()); // index
4179  ProcessInput<T>(node, 2,
4180  TruncatingUseInfoFromRepresentation(
4181  element_representation, access.type)); // value
4182  ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 3);
4183  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4184  if (lower<T>()) {
4185  if (write_barrier_kind < access.write_barrier_kind) {
4186  access.write_barrier_kind = write_barrier_kind;
4187  ChangeOp(node, jsgraph_->simplified()->StoreElement(access));
4188  }
4189  }
4190  return;
4191  }
4192  case IrOpcode::kNumberIsFloat64Hole: {
4193  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4194  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4195  return;
4196  }
4197  case IrOpcode::kTransitionAndStoreElement: {
4198  Type value_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(2));
4199 
4200  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // array
4201  ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::Word()); // index
4202 
4203  if (value_type.Is(Type::SignedSmall())) {
4204  ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32()); // value
4205  if (lower<T>()) {
4206  ChangeOp(node, simplified()->StoreSignedSmallElement());
4207  }
4208  } else if (value_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
4209  ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64()); // value
4210  if (lower<T>()) {
4211  MapRef double_map = DoubleMapParameterOf(node->op());
4212  ChangeOp(node,
4213  simplified()->TransitionAndStoreNumberElement(double_map));
4214  }
4215  } else if (value_type.Is(Type::NonNumber())) {
4216  ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // value
4217  if (lower<T>()) {
4218  MapRef fast_map = FastMapParameterOf(node->op());
4219  ChangeOp(node, simplified()->TransitionAndStoreNonNumberElement(
4220  fast_map, value_type));
4221  }
4222  } else {
4223  ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // value
4224  }
4225 
4226  ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 3);
4227  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4228  return;
4229  }
4230  case IrOpcode::kLoadTypedElement: {
4231  MachineRepresentation const rep =
4232  MachineRepresentationFromArrayType(ExternalArrayTypeOf(node->op()));
4233  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // buffer
4234  ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // base pointer
4235  ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::Word()); // external pointer
4236  ProcessInput<T>(node, 3, UseInfo::Word()); // index
4237  ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 4);

4239  return;

4244  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // object
4245  ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::Word()); // base
4246  ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::Word()); // index
4247  ProcessInput<T>(node, 3, UseInfo::Bool()); // little-endian
4248  ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 4);

4256  ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // base pointer

4277  }
4278  case IrOpcode::kConvertReceiver: {
4279  Type input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
4280  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // object
4281  ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // native_context
4282  ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // global_proxy
4283  ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 3);
4284  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4285  if (lower<T>()) {
4286  // Try to optimize the {node} based on the input type.
4287  if (input_type.Is(Type::Receiver())) {
4288  DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4289  } else if (input_type.Is(Type::NullOrUndefined())) {
4290  DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(2));
4291  } else if (!input_type.Maybe(Type::NullOrUndefined())) {
4292  ChangeOp(node, lowering->simplified()->ConvertReceiver(
4293  ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined));
4294  }
4295  }
4296  return;
4297  }
4298  case IrOpcode::kPlainPrimitiveToNumber: {
4299  if (InputIs(node, Type::Boolean())) {
4300  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Bool(), MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
4301  if (lower<T>()) {
4302  DeferReplacement(node, InsertSemanticsHintForVerifier(
4303  node->op(), node->InputAt(0)));
4304  }
4305  } else if (InputIs(node, Type::String())) {
4306  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4307  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4308  if (lower<T>()) {
4309  ChangeOp(node, simplified()->StringToNumber());
4310  }
4311  } else if (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
4312  if (InputIs(node, Type::NumberOrOddball())) {
4313  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
4314  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
4315  if (lower<T>()) {
4316  DeferReplacement(node, InsertSemanticsHintForVerifier(
4317  node->op(), node->InputAt(0)));
4318  }
4319  } else {

4321  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
4322  if (lower<T>()) {
4323  ChangeOp(node, simplified()->PlainPrimitiveToWord32());
4324  }
4325  }
4326  } else if (truncation.TruncatesOddballAndBigIntToNumber()) {
4327  if (InputIs(node, Type::NumberOrOddball())) {
4328  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4329  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
4330  if (lower<T>()) {
4331  DeferReplacement(node, InsertSemanticsHintForVerifier(
4332  node->op(), node->InputAt(0)));
4333  }
4334  } else {
4335  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4336  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);

4338  ChangeOp(node, simplified()->PlainPrimitiveToFloat64());
4339  }
4340  }

4342  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4343  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4344  }
4345  return;
4346  }
4347  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeToNumber: {
4348  NumberOperationParameters const& p =
4349  NumberOperationParametersOf(node->op());
4350  switch (p.hint()) {
4351  case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
4352  case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs:
4353  VisitUnop<T>(node,
4354  CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(
4355  p.hint(), kDistinguishZeros, p.feedback()),
4356  MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Signed32());
4357  break;
4358  case NumberOperationHint::kAdditiveSafeInteger:
4359  case NumberOperationHint::kNumber:
4360  case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrBoolean:
4361  case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball:
4362  VisitUnop<T>(
4363  node, CheckedUseInfoAsFloat64FromHint(p.hint(), p.feedback()),
4364  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
4365  break;
4366  }
4367  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4368  return;
4369  }
4370  case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeToBigInt: {
4371  if (truncation.IsUnused() && InputIs(node, Type::BigInt())) {
4372  VisitUnused<T>(node);
4373  return;
4374  }
4375  if (Is64() && truncation.IsUsedAsWord64()) {
4376  VisitUnop<T>(node,
4377  UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
4378  MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
4379  } else {
4380  BigIntOperationParameters const& p =
4381  BigIntOperationParametersOf(node->op());
4382  switch (p.hint()) {
4383  case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt64: {
4384  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::CheckedBigInt64AsWord64(p.feedback()),
4385  MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
4386  break;
4387  }
4388  case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt: {
4389  VisitUnop<T>(node,
4390  UseInfo::CheckedBigIntAsTaggedPointer(p.feedback()),
4391  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4392  }
4393  }
4394  }
4395  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4396  return;
4397  }
4398  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsArrayBufferView: {
4399  // TODO(turbofan): Introduce a Type::ArrayBufferView?
4400  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4401  return;
4402  }
4403  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsBigInt: {
4404  VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::BigInt(), lowering);
4405  return;
4406  }
4407  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsCallable: {
4408  VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::Callable(), lowering);
4409  return;
4410  }
4411  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsConstructor: {

4418  return;
4419  }
4420  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsFiniteNumber: {
4421  Type const input_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0));
4422  if (input_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger)) {
4423  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::None(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);

4426  node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4427  true_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(1)));

4434  false_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0)));
4435  }

4437  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),

4441  }
4442  } else {
4443  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);

4446  }
4447  case IrOpcode::kNumberIsFinite: {

4450  return;
4451  }
4452  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsSafeInteger: {
4453  Type const input_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0));
4454  if (input_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger)) {
4455  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::None(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4456  if (lower<T>()) {
4457  DeferReplacement(
4458  node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4459  true_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(1)));
4460  }
4461  } else if (!input_type.Maybe(Type::Number())) {
4462  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);

4466  false_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0)));

4479  case IrOpcode::kNumberIsSafeInteger: {
4480  UNREACHABLE();
4481  }
4482  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsInteger: {
4483  Type const input_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0));
4484  if (input_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger)) {
4485  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::None(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4486  if (lower<T>()) {
4487  DeferReplacement(
4488  node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4489  true_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(1)));
4490  }
4491  } else if (!input_type.Maybe(Type::Number())) {
4492  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4493  if (lower<T>()) {
4494  DeferReplacement(
4495  node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4496  false_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0)));
4497  }
4498  } else if (input_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
4499  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4500  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4501  if (lower<T>()) {
4502  ChangeOp(node, lowering->simplified()->NumberIsInteger());
4503  }
4504  } else {
4505  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4506  }
4507  return;
4508  }
4509  case IrOpcode::kNumberIsInteger: {
4510  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4511  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4512  return;
4513  }
4514  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsMinusZero: {
4515  Type const input_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0));
4516  if (input_type.Is(Type::MinusZero())) {
4517  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::None(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4518  if (lower<T>()) {
4519  DeferReplacement(
4520  node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4521  true_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(1)));
4522  }
4523  } else if (!input_type.Maybe(Type::MinusZero())) {
4524  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4525  if (lower<T>()) {
4526  DeferReplacement(
4527  node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4528  false_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0)));
4529  }
4530  } else if (input_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
4531  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4532  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4533  if (lower<T>()) {
4534  ChangeOp(node, simplified()->NumberIsMinusZero());
4535  }
4536  } else {
4537  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4538  }
4539  return;
4540  }
4541  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsNaN: {
4542  Type const input_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0));
4543  if (input_type.Is(Type::NaN())) {
4544  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::None(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4545  if (lower<T>()) {
4546  DeferReplacement(
4547  node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4548  true_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(1)));
4549  }
4550  } else if (!input_type.Maybe(Type::NaN())) {
4551  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4552  if (lower<T>()) {
4553  DeferReplacement(
4554  node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4555  false_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0)));
4556  }
4557  } else if (input_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
4558  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4559  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4560  if (lower<T>()) {
4561  ChangeOp(node, simplified()->NumberIsNaN());
4562  }
4563  } else {
4564  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4565  }
4566  return;
4567  }
4568  case IrOpcode::kNumberIsNaN: {
4569  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4570  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4571  return;
4572  }
4573  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsNonCallable: {
4574  VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::NonCallable(), lowering);
4575  return;
4576  }
4577  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsNumber: {
4578  VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::Number(), lowering);
4579  return;
4580  }
4581  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsReceiver: {
4582  VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::Receiver(), lowering);
4583  return;
4584  }
4585  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsSmi: {
4586  // TODO(turbofan): Optimize based on input representation.
4587  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4588  return;
4589  }
4590  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsString: {
4591  VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::String(), lowering);
4592  return;
4593  }
4594  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsSymbol: {
4595  VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::Symbol(), lowering);
4596  return;
4597  }
4598  case IrOpcode::kObjectIsUndetectable: {
4599  VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::Undetectable(), lowering);
4600  return;
4601  }
4602  case IrOpcode::kArgumentsLength:
4603  case IrOpcode::kRestLength: {
4604  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned);
4605  return;
4606  }
4607  case IrOpcode::kNewDoubleElements:
4608  case IrOpcode::kNewSmiOrObjectElements: {
4609  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Word(),
4610  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4611  return;
4612  }
4613  case IrOpcode::kNewArgumentsElements: {
4614  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TaggedSigned(),
4615  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4616  return;
4617  }
4618  case IrOpcode::kCheckFloat64Hole: {
4619  Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
4620  CheckFloat64HoleMode mode =
4621  CheckFloat64HoleParametersOf(node->op()).mode();
4622  if (mode == CheckFloat64HoleMode::kAllowReturnHole) {
4623  // If {mode} is allow-return-hole _and_ the {truncation}
4624  // identifies NaN and undefined, we can just pass along
4625  // the {truncation} and completely wipe the {node}.
4626  if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
4627  if (truncation.TruncatesOddballAndBigIntToNumber()) {
4628  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4629  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
4630  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4631  return;
4632  }
4633  }
4634  VisitUnop<T>(
4635  node, UseInfo(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, Truncation::Any()),
4636  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, Type::Number());
4637  if (lower<T>() && input_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
4638  DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4639  }
4640  return;
4641  }
4642  case IrOpcode::kChangeFloat64HoleToTagged: {
4643  // If the {truncation} identifies NaN and undefined, we can just pass
4644  // along the {truncation} and completely wipe the {node}.
4645  if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
4646  if (truncation.TruncatesOddballAndBigIntToNumber()) {
4647  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4648  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
4649  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4650  return;
4651  }
4652  VisitUnop<T>(
4653  node, UseInfo(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, Truncation::Any()),
4654  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4655  return;
4656  }
4657  case IrOpcode::kChangeFloat64OrUndefinedOrHoleToTagged: {
4658  // TODO(nicohartmann): Consider using truncation.
4659  VisitUnop<T>(node,
4660  UseInfo(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64,
4661  Truncation::BooleanAndNullAndBigIntToNumber()),
4662  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4663  return;
4664  }
4665  case IrOpcode::kCheckNotTaggedHole: {
4666  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4667  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4668  return;
4669  }
4670  case IrOpcode::kCheckClosure: {
4671  VisitUnop<T>(
4672  node, UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource()),
4673  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4674  return;
4675  }
4676  case IrOpcode::kConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined: {
4677  if (InputIs(node, Type::NumberOrHole()) &&
4678  truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() && !truncation.check_safe_integer()) {
4679  // Propagate the Word32 truncation.
4680  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
4681  MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
4682  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4683  } else if (InputIs(node, Type::NumberOrHole()) &&
4684  truncation.TruncatesOddballAndBigIntToNumber()) {
4685  // Propagate the Float64 truncation.
4686  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4687  MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
4688  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4689  } else if (InputIs(node, Type::NumberOrUndefinedOrHole()) &&
4690  truncation.TruncatesBooleanAndNullAndBigIntToNumber()) {
4691  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4692  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4693  } else if (InputIs(node, Type::NonInternal())) {
4694  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4695  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4696  if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4697  } else {
4698  // TODO(turbofan): Add a (Tagged) truncation that identifies hole
4699  // and undefined, i.e. for a[i] === obj cases.
4700  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4701  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4702  }
4703  return;
4704  }
4705  case IrOpcode::kCheckEqualsSymbol:
4706  case IrOpcode::kCheckEqualsInternalizedString:
4707  return VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4708  MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4709  case IrOpcode::kMapGuard:
4710  // Eliminate MapGuard nodes here.
4711  return VisitUnused<T>(node);
4712  case IrOpcode::kCheckMaps: {
4713  CheckMapsParameters const& p = CheckMapsParametersOf(node->op());
4714  return VisitUnop<T>(
4715  node, UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(p.feedback()),
4716  MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4717  }
4718  case IrOpcode::kTransitionElementsKind: {
4719  return VisitUnop<T>(
4720  node, UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource()),
4721  MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4722  }
4723  case IrOpcode::kTransitionElementsKindOrCheckMap: {
4724  return VisitUnop<T>(
4725  node, UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource()),
4726  MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4727  }
4728  case IrOpcode::kCompareMaps:
4729  return VisitUnop<T>(
4730  node, UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource()),
4731  MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4732  case IrOpcode::kEnsureWritableFastElements:
4733  return VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4734  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4735  case IrOpcode::kMaybeGrowFastElements: {
4736  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // object
4737  ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // elements
4738  ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32()); // index
4739  ProcessInput<T>(node, 3, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32()); // length
4740  ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 4);
4741  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4742  return;
4743  }
4744 
4745  case IrOpcode::kDateNow:
4746  VisitInputs<T>(node);
4747  return SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4748  case IrOpcode::kDoubleArrayMax: {
4749  return VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4750  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4751  }
4752  case IrOpcode::kDoubleArrayMin: {
4753  return VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4754  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4755  }
4756  case IrOpcode::kFrameState:
4757  return VisitFrameState<T>(FrameState{node});
4758  case IrOpcode::kStateValues:
4759  return VisitStateValues<T>(node);
4760  case IrOpcode::kObjectState:
4761  return VisitObjectState<T>(node);
4762  case IrOpcode::kObjectId:
4763  return SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4764 
4765  case IrOpcode::kTypeGuard: {
4766  if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
4767 
4768  // We just get rid of the sigma here, choosing the best representation
4769  // for the sigma's type.
4770  Type type = TypeOf(node);
4771  MachineRepresentation representation =
4772  GetOutputInfoForPhi(type, truncation);
4773 
4774  // Here we pretend that the input has the sigma's type for the
4775  // conversion.
4776  UseInfo use(representation, truncation);
4777  if (propagate<T>()) {
4778  EnqueueInput<T>(node, 0, use);
4779  } else if (lower<T>()) {
4780  ConvertInput(node, 0, use, type);
4781  }
4782  ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 1);
4783  SetOutput<T>(node, representation);
4784  return;
4785  }
4786 
4787  case IrOpcode::kFinishRegion:
4788  VisitInputs<T>(node);
4789  // Assume the output is tagged pointer.
4790  return SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4791 
4792  case IrOpcode::kReturn:
4793  VisitReturn<T>(node);
4794  // Assume the output is tagged.
4795  return SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4796 
4797  case IrOpcode::kFindOrderedHashMapEntry: {
4798  Type const key_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
4799  if (key_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero())) {
4800  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
4801  MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
4802  if (lower<T>()) {
4803  ChangeOp(
4804  node,
4805  lowering->simplified()->FindOrderedHashMapEntryForInt32Key());
4806  }
4807  } else {
4808  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4809  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned);
4810  }
4811  return;
4812  }
4813 
4814  case IrOpcode::kFindOrderedHashSetEntry:
4815  VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4816  MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned);
4817  return;
4818 
4819  case IrOpcode::kFastApiCall: {
4820  VisitFastApiCall<T>(node, lowering);
4821  return;
4822  }
4823 
4824  // Operators with all inputs tagged and no or tagged output have uniform
4825  // handling.
4826  case IrOpcode::kEnd:
4827  case IrOpcode::kIfSuccess:
4828  case IrOpcode::kIfException:
4829  case IrOpcode::kIfTrue:
4830  case IrOpcode::kIfFalse:
4831  case IrOpcode::kIfValue:
4832  case IrOpcode::kIfDefault:
4833  case IrOpcode::kDeoptimize:
4834  case IrOpcode::kEffectPhi:
4835  case IrOpcode::kTerminate:
4836  case IrOpcode::kCheckpoint:
4837  case IrOpcode::kLoop:
4838  case IrOpcode::kMerge:
4839  case IrOpcode::kThrow:
4840  case IrOpcode::kBeginRegion:
4841  case IrOpcode::kProjection:
4842  case IrOpcode::kOsrValue:
4843  case IrOpcode::kArgumentsElementsState:
4844  case IrOpcode::kArgumentsLengthState:
4845  case IrOpcode::kUnreachable:
4846  case IrOpcode::kRuntimeAbort:
4847 // All JavaScript operators except JSToNumber, JSToNumberConvertBigInt,
4848 // kJSToNumeric and JSWasmCall have uniform handling.
4849 #define OPCODE_CASE(name, ...) case IrOpcode::k##name:
4850  JS_SIMPLE_BINOP_LIST(OPCODE_CASE)
4851  JS_OBJECT_OP_LIST(OPCODE_CASE)
4852  JS_CONTEXT_OP_LIST(OPCODE_CASE)
4853  JS_OTHER_OP_LIST(OPCODE_CASE)
4854 #undef OPCODE_CASE
4855  case IrOpcode::kJSBitwiseNot:
4856  case IrOpcode::kJSDecrement:
4857  case IrOpcode::kJSIncrement:
4858  case IrOpcode::kJSNegate:
4859  case IrOpcode::kJSToLength:
4860  case IrOpcode::kJSToName:
4861  case IrOpcode::kJSToObject:
4862  case IrOpcode::kJSToString:
4863  case IrOpcode::kJSParseInt:
4864 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4865  if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSWasmCall) {
4866  return VisitJSWasmCall<T>(node, lowering);
4867  }
4868 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4869  VisitInputs<T>(node);
4870  // Assume the output is tagged.
4871  return SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4872  case IrOpcode::kDeadValue:
4873  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Any());
4874  return SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4875  case IrOpcode::kStaticAssert:
4876  DCHECK(TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Boolean()));
4877  return VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Bool(),
4878  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4879  case IrOpcode::kAssertType:
4880  return VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4881  MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4882  case IrOpcode::kVerifyType: {
4883  Type inputType = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
4884  VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kTagged,
4885  inputType);
4886  if (lower<T>()) {
4887  if (inputType.CanBeAsserted()) {
4888  ChangeOp(node, simplified()->AssertType(inputType));
4889  } else {
4890  if (!v8_flags.fuzzing) {
4891 #ifdef DEBUG
4892  inputType.Print();
4893 #endif
4894  FATAL("%%VerifyType: unsupported type");
4895  }
4896  DisconnectFromEffectAndControl(node);
4897  }
4898  }
4899  return;
4900  }
4901  case IrOpcode::kCheckTurboshaftTypeOf: {
4902  NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node->InputAt(0));
4903  MachineRepresentation input_rep = info->representation();
4904  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo{input_rep, Truncation::None()});
4905  ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::Any());
4906  SetOutput<T>(node, input_rep);
4907  return;
4908  }
4909  case IrOpcode::kDebugBreak:
4910  return;
4911 
4912  // Nodes from machine graphs.
4913  case IrOpcode::kEnterMachineGraph: {
4914  DCHECK_EQ(1, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
4915  UseInfo use_info = OpParameter<UseInfo>(node->op());
4916  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, use_info);
4917  SetOutput<T>(node, use_info.representation());
4918  if (lower<T>()) {
4919  DeferReplacement(node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4920  Type::Machine(), node->InputAt(0)));
4921  }
4922  return;
4923  }
4924  case IrOpcode::kExitMachineGraph: {
4925  DCHECK_EQ(1, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
4926  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Any());
4927  const auto& p = ExitMachineGraphParametersOf(node->op());
4928  SetOutput<T>(node, p.output_representation(), p.output_type());
4929  if (lower<T>()) {
4930  DeferReplacement(node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4931  p.output_type(), node->InputAt(0)));
4932  }
4933  return;
4934  }
4935  case IrOpcode::kInt32Add:
4936  case IrOpcode::kInt32LessThanOrEqual:
4937  case IrOpcode::kInt32Sub:
4938  case IrOpcode::kUint32LessThan:
4939  case IrOpcode::kUint32LessThanOrEqual:
4940  case IrOpcode::kUint64LessThan:
4941  case IrOpcode::kUint64LessThanOrEqual:
4942  case IrOpcode::kUint32Div:
4943  case IrOpcode::kWord32And:
4944  case IrOpcode::kWord32Equal:
4945  case IrOpcode::kWord32Or:
4946  case IrOpcode::kWord32Shl:
4947  case IrOpcode::kWord32Shr:
4948  for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); ++i) {
4949  ProcessInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::Any());
4950  }
4951  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
4952  return;
4953  case IrOpcode::kInt64Add:
4954  case IrOpcode::kInt64Sub:
4955  case IrOpcode::kUint64Div:
4956  case IrOpcode::kWord64And:
4957  case IrOpcode::kWord64Shl:
4958  case IrOpcode::kWord64Shr:
4959  case IrOpcode::kChangeUint32ToUint64:
4960  for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); ++i) {
4961  ProcessInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::Any());
4962  }
4963  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
4964  return;
4965  case IrOpcode::kLoad:
4966  for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); ++i) {
4967  ProcessInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::Any());
4968  }
4969  SetOutput<T>(node, LoadRepresentationOf(node->op()).representation());
4970  return;
4971 
4972 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
4973  case IrOpcode::kGetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData:
4974  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4975  return;
4976 
4977  case IrOpcode::kSetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData:
4978  ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
4979  SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4980  return;
4981 #endif // V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
4982 
4983  default:
4984  FATAL(
4985  "Representation inference: unsupported opcode %i (%s), node #%i\n.",
4986  node->opcode(), node->op()->mnemonic(), node->id());
4987  break;
4988  }
4989  UNREACHABLE();
4990  }
4991 
4992  void DisconnectFromEffectAndControl(Node* node) {
4993  if (node->op()->EffectInputCount() == 1) {
4994  Node* control;
4995  if (node->op()->ControlInputCount() == 1) {
4996  control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
4997  } else {
4998  DCHECK_EQ(node->op()->ControlInputCount(), 0);
4999  control = nullptr;
5000  }
5001  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
5002  ReplaceEffectControlUses(node, effect, control);
5003  } else {
5004  DCHECK_EQ(0, node->op()->EffectInputCount());
5005  DCHECK_EQ(0, node->op()->ControlOutputCount());
5006  DCHECK_EQ(0, node->op()->EffectOutputCount());
5007  }
5008  }
5009 
5010  void DeferReplacement(Node* node, Node* replacement) {
5011  TRACE("defer replacement #%d:%s with #%d:%s\n", node->id(),
5012  node->op()->mnemonic(), replacement->id(),
5013  replacement->op()->mnemonic());
5014 
5015  DisconnectFromEffectAndControl(node);
5016  node->NullAllInputs(); // Node is now dead.
5017 
5018  replacements_.push_back(node);
5019  replacements_.push_back(replacement);
5020 
5021  NotifyNodeReplaced(node, replacement);
5022  }
5023 
5024  Node* InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(const Type& type, Node* node) {
5025  if (V8_UNLIKELY(verification_enabled())) {
5026  DCHECK(!type.IsInvalid());
5027  node = graph()->NewNode(common()->SLVerifierHint(nullptr, type), node);
5028  verifier_->RecordHint(node);
5029  }
5030  return node;
5031  }
5032 
5033  Node* InsertUnconditionalDeopt(Node* node, DeoptimizeReason reason,
5034  const FeedbackSource& feedback = {}) {
5035  Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
5036  Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
5037  effect =
5038  jsgraph_->graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckIf(reason, feedback),
5039  jsgraph_->Int32Constant(0), effect, control);
5040  Node* unreachable = effect = jsgraph_->graph()->NewNode(
5041  jsgraph_->common()->Unreachable(), effect, control);
5042  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
5043  return unreachable;
5044  }
5045 
5046  Node* InsertSemanticsHintForVerifier(const Operator* semantics, Node* node) {
5047  if (V8_UNLIKELY(verification_enabled())) {
5048  node = graph()->NewNode(common()->SLVerifierHint(semantics, {}), node);
5049  verifier_->RecordHint(node);
5050  }
5051  return node;
5052  }
5053 
5054  private:
5055  void ChangeOp(Node* node, const Operator* new_op) {
5056  compiler::NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, new_op);
5057 
5058  if (V8_UNLIKELY(observe_node_manager_ != nullptr))
5059  observe_node_manager_->OnNodeChanged(kSimplifiedLoweringReducerName, node,
5060  node);
5061  }
5062 
5063  void NotifyNodeReplaced(Node* node, Node* replacement) {
5064  if (V8_UNLIKELY(observe_node_manager_ != nullptr))
5065  observe_node_manager_->OnNodeChanged(kSimplifiedLoweringReducerName, node,
5066  replacement);
5067  }
5068 
5069  Type true_type() const { return singleton_true_; }
5070  Type false_type() const { return singleton_false_; }
5071 
5072  JSGraph* jsgraph_;
5073  JSHeapBroker* broker_;
5074  Zone* zone_; // Temporary zone.
5075  // Map from node to its uses that might need to be revisited.
5076  ZoneMap<Node*, ZoneVector<Node*>> might_need_revisit_;
5077  size_t count_; // number of nodes in the graph
5078  ZoneVector<NodeInfo> info_; // node id -> usage information
5079 #ifdef DEBUG
5080  ZoneVector<InputUseInfos> node_input_use_infos_; // Debug information about
5081  // requirements on inputs.
5082 #endif // DEBUG
5083  NodeVector replacements_; // replacements to be done after lowering
5084  RepresentationChanger* changer_; // for inserting representation changes
5085  ZoneQueue<Node*> revisit_queue_; // Queue for revisiting nodes.
5086 
5087  struct NodeState {
5088  Node* node;
5089  int input_index;
5090  };
5091  NodeVector traversal_nodes_; // Order in which to traverse the nodes.
5092  // TODO(danno): RepresentationSelector shouldn't know anything about the
5093  // source positions table, but must for now since there currently is no other
5094  // way to pass down source position information to nodes created during
5095  // lowering. Once this phase becomes a vanilla reducer, it should get source
5096  // position information via the SourcePositionWrapper like all other reducers.
5097  SourcePositionTable* source_positions_;
5098  NodeOriginTable* node_origins_;
5099  TypeCache const* type_cache_;
5100  OperationTyper op_typer_; // helper for the feedback typer
5101  Type singleton_true_;
5102  Type singleton_false_;
5103  TickCounter* const tick_counter_;
5104  Linkage* const linkage_;
5105  ObserveNodeManager* const observe_node_manager_;
5106  SimplifiedLoweringVerifier* verifier_; // Used to verify output graph.
5107 
5108  NodeInfo* GetInfo(Node* node) {
5109  DCHECK(node->id() < count_);
5110  return &info_[node->id()];
5111  }
5112  Zone* zone() { return zone_; }
5113  Zone* graph_zone() { return jsgraph_->zone(); }
5114  Linkage* linkage() { return linkage_; }
5115 };
5116 
5117 // Template specializations
5118 
5119 // Enqueue {use_node}'s {index} input if the {use_info} contains new information
5120 // for that input node.
5121 template <>
5122 void RepresentationSelector::EnqueueInput<PROPAGATE>(Node* use_node, int index,
5123  UseInfo use_info) {
5124  Node* node = use_node->InputAt(index);
5125  NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
5126 #ifdef DEBUG
5127  // Check monotonicity of input requirements.
5128  node_input_use_infos_[use_node->id()].SetAndCheckInput(use_node, index,
5129  use_info);
5130 #endif // DEBUG
5131  if (info->unvisited()) {
5132  info->AddUse(use_info);
5133  TRACE(" initial #%i: %s\n", node->id(), info->truncation().description());
5134  return;
5135  }
5136  TRACE(" queue #%i?: %s\n", node->id(), info->truncation().description());
5137  if (info->AddUse(use_info)) {
5138  // New usage information for the node is available.
5139  if (!info->queued()) {
5140  DCHECK(info->visited());
5141  revisit_queue_.push(node);
5142  info->set_queued();
5143  TRACE(" added: %s\n", info->truncation().description());
5144  } else {
5145  TRACE(" inqueue: %s\n", info->truncation().description());
5146  }
5147  }
5148 }
5149 
5150 template <>
5151 void RepresentationSelector::SetOutput<PROPAGATE>(
5152  Node* node, MachineRepresentation representation, Type restriction_type) {
5153  NodeInfo* const info = GetInfo(node);
5154  info->set_restriction_type(restriction_type);
5155 }
5156 
5157 template <>
5158 void RepresentationSelector::SetOutput<RETYPE>(
5159  Node* node, MachineRepresentation representation, Type restriction_type) {
5160  NodeInfo* const info = GetInfo(node);
5161  Type node_static_type = NodeProperties::GetTypeOrAny(node);
5162  DCHECK(Type::Intersect(restriction_type, node_static_type, zone_)
5163  .Is(info->restriction_type()));
5164  USE(node_static_type);
5165  info->set_output(representation);
5166 }
5167 
5168 template <>
5169 void RepresentationSelector::SetOutput<LOWER>(
5170  Node* node, MachineRepresentation representation, Type restriction_type) {
5171  NodeInfo* const info = GetInfo(node);
5172  Type node_static_type = NodeProperties::GetTypeOrAny(node);
5173  DCHECK_EQ(info->representation(), representation);
5174  DCHECK(Type::Intersect(restriction_type, node_static_type, zone_)
5175  .Is(info->restriction_type()));
5176  USE(node_static_type);
5177  USE(info);
5178 }
5179 
5180 template <>
5181 void RepresentationSelector::ProcessInput<PROPAGATE>(Node* node, int index,
5182  UseInfo use) {
5183  DCHECK_IMPLIES(use.type_check() != TypeCheckKind::kNone,
5184  !node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoDeopt) &&
5185  node->op()->EffectInputCount() > 0);
5186  EnqueueInput<PROPAGATE>(node, index, use);
5187 }
5188 
5189 template <>
5190 void RepresentationSelector::ProcessInput<RETYPE>(Node* node, int index,
5191  UseInfo use) {
5192  DCHECK_IMPLIES(use.type_check() != TypeCheckKind::kNone,
5193  !node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoDeopt) &&
5194  node->op()->EffectInputCount() > 0);
5195 }
5196 
5197 template <>
5198 void RepresentationSelector::ProcessInput<LOWER>(Node* node, int index,
5199  UseInfo use) {
5200  DCHECK_IMPLIES(use.type_check() != TypeCheckKind::kNone,
5201  !node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoDeopt) &&
5202  node->op()->EffectInputCount() > 0);
5203  ConvertInput(node, index, use);
5204 }
5205 
5206 template <>
5207 void RepresentationSelector::ProcessRemainingInputs<PROPAGATE>(Node* node,
5208  int index) {
5209  DCHECK_GE(index, NodeProperties::PastContextIndex(node));
5210 
5211  // Enqueue other inputs (effects, control).
5212  for (int i = std::max(index, NodeProperties::FirstEffectIndex(node));
5213  i < node->InputCount(); ++i) {
5214  EnqueueInput<PROPAGATE>(node, i);
5215  }
5216 }
5217 
5218 // The default, most general visitation case. For {node}, process all value,
5219 // context, frame state, effect, and control inputs, assuming that value
5220 // inputs should have {kRepTagged} representation and can observe all output
5221 // values {kTypeAny}.
5222 template <>
5223 void RepresentationSelector::VisitInputs<PROPAGATE>(Node* node) {
5224  int first_effect_index = NodeProperties::FirstEffectIndex(node);
5225  // Visit value, context and frame state inputs as tagged.
5226  for (int i = 0; i < first_effect_index; i++) {
5227  ProcessInput<PROPAGATE>(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
5228  }
5229  // Only enqueue other inputs (effects, control).
5230  for (int i = first_effect_index; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
5231  EnqueueInput<PROPAGATE>(node, i);
5232  }
5233 }
5234 
5235 template <>
5236 void RepresentationSelector::VisitInputs<LOWER>(Node* node) {
5237  int first_effect_index = NodeProperties::FirstEffectIndex(node);
5238  // Visit value, context and frame state inputs as tagged.
5239  for (int i = 0; i < first_effect_index; i++) {
5240  ProcessInput<LOWER>(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
5241  }
5242 }
5243 
5244 template <>
5245 void RepresentationSelector::InsertUnreachableIfNecessary<LOWER>(Node* node) {
5246  // If the node is effectful and it produces an impossible value, then we
5247  // insert Unreachable node after it.
5248  if (node->op()->ValueOutputCount() > 0 &&
5249  node->op()->EffectOutputCount() > 0 &&
5250  node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kUnreachable && TypeOf(node).IsNone()) {
5251  Node* control = (node->op()->ControlOutputCount() == 0)
5252  ? NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node, 0)
5253  : NodeProperties::FindSuccessfulControlProjection(node);
5254 
5255  Node* unreachable =
5256  graph()->NewNode(common()->Unreachable(), node, control);
5257 
5258  // Insert unreachable node and replace all the effect uses of the {node}
5259  // with the new unreachable node.
5260  for (Edge edge : node->use_edges()) {
5261  if (!NodeProperties::IsEffectEdge(edge)) continue;
5262  // Make sure to not overwrite the unreachable node's input. That would
5263  // create a cycle.
5264  if (edge.from() == unreachable) continue;
5265  // Avoid messing up the exceptional path.
5266  if (edge.from()->opcode() == IrOpcode::kIfException) {
5267  DCHECK(!node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoThrow));
5268  DCHECK_EQ(NodeProperties::GetControlInput(edge.from()), node);
5269  continue;
5270  }
5271 
5272  edge.UpdateTo(unreachable);
5273  }
5274  }
5275 }

5281  ObserveNodeManager* observe_node_manager)

5285  type_cache_(TypeCache::Get()),
5286  source_positions_(source_positions),

5288  tick_counter_(tick_counter),
5289  linkage_(linkage),
5290  info_(info),
5291  observe_node_manager_(observe_node_manager) {}

5293 void SimplifiedLowering::LowerAllNodes() {
5294  SimplifiedLoweringVerifier* verifier = nullptr;
5295  if (v8_flags.verify_simplified_lowering) {
5296  verifier = zone_->New<SimplifiedLoweringVerifier>(zone_, graph());
5297  }
5298  RepresentationChanger changer(jsgraph(), broker_, verifier);
5299  RepresentationSelector selector(
5300  jsgraph(), broker_, zone_, &changer, source_positions_, node_origins_,
5301  tick_counter_, linkage_, observe_node_manager_, verifier);
5302  selector.Run(this);
5303 }
5304 
5305 void SimplifiedLowering::DoJSToNumberOrNumericTruncatesToFloat64(
5306  Node* node, RepresentationSelector* selector) {
5307  DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumber ||
5308  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumberConvertBigInt ||
5309  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumeric);
5310  Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
5311  Node* context = node->InputAt(1);
5312  Node* frame_state = node->InputAt(2);
5313  Node* effect = node->InputAt(3);
5314  Node* control = node->InputAt(4);
5315 
5316  Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), value);
5317  Node* branch0 = graph()->NewNode(
5318  common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check0,
5319  control);
5320 
5321  Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
5322  Node* etrue0 = effect;
5323  Node* vtrue0;
5324  {
5325  vtrue0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ChangeTaggedSignedToInt32(), value);
5326  vtrue0 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->ChangeInt32ToFloat64(), vtrue0);
5327  }
5328 
5329  Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
5330  Node* efalse0 = effect;
5331  Node* vfalse0;
5332  {
5333  Operator const* op =
5334  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumber
5335  ? (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumberConvertBigInt
5336  ? ToNumberConvertBigIntOperator()
5337  : ToNumberOperator())
5338  : ToNumericOperator();
5339  Node* code = node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumber
5340  ? ToNumberCode()
5341  : (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumberConvertBigInt
5342  ? ToNumberConvertBigIntCode()
5343  : ToNumericCode());
5344  vfalse0 = efalse0 = if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(
5345  op, code, value, context, frame_state, efalse0, if_false0);
5346 
5347  // Update potential {IfException} uses of {node} to point to the above
5348  // stub call node instead.
5349  Node* on_exception = nullptr;
5350  if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
5351  NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(on_exception, vfalse0);
5352  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(on_exception, efalse0);
5353  if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), vfalse0);
5354  }
5355 
5356  Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), vfalse0);
5357  Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(
5358  common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check1,
5359  if_false0);
5360 
5361  Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
5362  Node* etrue1 = efalse0;
5363  Node* vtrue1;
5364  {
5365  vtrue1 =
5366  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ChangeTaggedSignedToInt32(), vfalse0);
5367  vtrue1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->ChangeInt32ToFloat64(), vtrue1);
5368  }
5369 
5370  Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
5371  Node* efalse1 = efalse0;
5372  Node* vfalse1;
5373  {
5374  vfalse1 = efalse1 = graph()->NewNode(
5375  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue()), efalse0,
5376  efalse1, if_false1);
5377  }
5378 
5379  if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true1, if_false1);
5380  efalse0 =
5381  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue1, efalse1, if_false0);
5382  vfalse0 =
5383  graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, 2),
5384  vtrue1, vfalse1, if_false0);
5385  }
5386 
5387  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true0, if_false0);
5388  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue0, efalse0, control);
5389  value = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, 2),
5390  vtrue0, vfalse0, control);
5391 
5392  // Replace effect and control uses appropriately.
5393  for (Edge edge : node->use_edges()) {
5394  if (NodeProperties::IsControlEdge(edge)) {
5395  if (edge.from()->opcode() == IrOpcode::kIfSuccess) {
5396  edge.from()->ReplaceUses(control);
5397  edge.from()->Kill();
5398  } else {
5399  DCHECK_NE(IrOpcode::kIfException, edge.from()->opcode());
5400  edge.UpdateTo(control);
5401  }
5402  } else if (NodeProperties::IsEffectEdge(edge)) {
5403  edge.UpdateTo(effect);
5404  }
5405  }
5406 
5407  selector->DeferReplacement(node, value);
5408 }
5409 
5410 void SimplifiedLowering::DoJSToNumberOrNumericTruncatesToWord32(
5411  Node* node, RepresentationSelector* selector) {
5412  DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumber ||
5413  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumberConvertBigInt ||
5414  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumeric);
5415  Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
5416  Node* context = node->InputAt(1);
5417  Node* frame_state = node->InputAt(2);
5418  Node* effect = node->InputAt(3);
5419  Node* control = node->InputAt(4);
5420 
5421  Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), value);
5422  Node* branch0 = graph()->NewNode(
5423  common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check0,
5424  control);
5425 
5426  Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
5427  Node* etrue0 = effect;
5428  Node* vtrue0 =
5429  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ChangeTaggedSignedToInt32(), value);
5430 
5431  Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
5432  Node* efalse0 = effect;
5433  Node* vfalse0;
5434  {
5435  Operator const* op =
5436  node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumber
5437  ? (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumberConvertBigInt
5438  ? ToNumberConvertBigIntOperator()
5439  : ToNumberOperator())
5440  : ToNumericOperator();
5441  Node* code = node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumber
5442  ? ToNumberCode()
5443  : (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumberConvertBigInt
5444  ? ToNumberConvertBigIntCode()
5445  : ToNumericCode());
5446  vfalse0 = efalse0 = if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(
5447  op, code, value, context, frame_state, efalse0, if_false0);
5448 
5449  // Update potential {IfException} uses of {node} to point to the above
5450  // stub call node instead.
5451  Node* on_exception = nullptr;
5452  if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
5453  NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(on_exception, vfalse0);
5454  NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(on_exception, efalse0);
5455  if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), vfalse0);
5456  }
5457 
5458  Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), vfalse0);
5459  Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(
5460  common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check1,
5461  if_false0);
5462 
5463  Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
5464  Node* etrue1 = efalse0;
5465  Node* vtrue1 =
5466  graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ChangeTaggedSignedToInt32(), vfalse0);
5467 
5468  Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
5469  Node* efalse1 = efalse0;
5470  Node* vfalse1;
5471  {
5472  vfalse1 = efalse1 = graph()->NewNode(
5473  simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue()), efalse0,
5474  efalse1, if_false1);
5475  vfalse1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->TruncateFloat64ToWord32(), vfalse1);
5476  }
5477 
5478  if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true1, if_false1);
5479  efalse0 =
5480  graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue1, efalse1, if_false0);
5481  vfalse0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, 2),
5482  vtrue1, vfalse1, if_false0);
5483  }
5484 
5485  control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true0, if_false0);
5486  effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue0, efalse0, control);
5487  value = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, 2),
5488  vtrue0, vfalse0, control);
5489 
5490  // Replace effect and control uses appropriately.
5491  for (Edge edge : node->use_edges()) {
5492  if (NodeProperties::IsControlEdge(edge)) {
5493  if (edge.from()->opcode() == IrOpcode::kIfSuccess) {
5494  edge.from()->ReplaceUses(control);
5495  edge.from()->Kill();
5496  } else {
5497  DCHECK_NE(IrOpcode::kIfException, edge.from()->opcode());
5498  edge.UpdateTo(control);
5499  }
5500  } else if (NodeProperties::IsEffectEdge(edge)) {
5501  edge.UpdateTo(effect);
5502  }
5503  }
5504 
5505  selector->DeferReplacement(node, value);
5506 }

5508 Node* SimplifiedLowering::Float64Round(Node* const node) {
5509  Node* const one = jsgraph()->Float64Constant(1.0);
5510  Node* const one_half = jsgraph()->Float64Constant(0.5);
5511  Node* const input = node->InputAt(0);
5512 
5513  // Round up towards Infinity, and adjust if the difference exceeds 0.5.
5514  Node* result = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Float64RoundUp().placeholder(),
5515  node->InputAt(0));
5516  return graph()->NewNode(
5517  common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64),
5518  graph()->NewNode(
5519  machine()->Float64LessThanOrEqual(),
5520  graph()->NewNode(machine()->Float64Sub(), result, one_half), input),
5521  result, graph()->NewNode(machine()->Float64Sub(), result, one));
5522 }
5523 
5524 Node* SimplifiedLowering::Float64Sign(Node* const node) {
5525  Node* const minus_one = jsgraph()->Float64Constant(-1.0);
5526  Node* const zero = jsgraph()->Float64Constant(0.0);
5527  Node* const one = jsgraph()->Float64Constant(1.0);
5528 
5529  Node* const input = node->InputAt(0);
5530 
5531  return graph()->NewNode(
5532  common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64),
5533  graph()->NewNode(machine()->Float64LessThan(), input, zero), minus_one,
5534  graph()->NewNode(
5535  common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64),
5536  graph()->NewNode(machine()->Float64LessThan(), zero, input), one,
5537  input));
5538 }
