5540 Node* SimplifiedLowering::Int32Abs(Node* const node) {
5541  Node* const input = node->InputAt(0);
5542 
5543  // Generate case for absolute integer value.
5544  //
5545  // let sign = input >> 31 in
5546  // (input ^ sign) - sign
5547 
5548  Node* sign = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32Sar(), input,
5549  jsgraph()->Int32Constant(31));
5550  return graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Sub(),
5551  graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32Xor(), input, sign),
5552  sign);
5553 }
5554 
5555 Node* SimplifiedLowering::Int32Div(Node* const node) {
5556  Int32BinopMatcher m(node);
5557  Node* const zero = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0);
5558  Node* const minus_one = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(-1);
5559  Node* const lhs = m.left().node();
5560  Node* const rhs = m.right().node();
5561 
5562  if (m.right().Is(-1)) {
5563  return graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Sub(), zero, lhs);
5564  } else if (m.right().Is(0)) {
5565  return rhs;
5566  } else if (machine()->Int32DivIsSafe() || m.right().HasResolvedValue()) {
5567  return graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Div(), lhs, rhs, graph()->start());
5568  }
5569 
5570  // General case for signed integer division.
5571  //
5572  // if 0 < rhs then
5573  // lhs / rhs
5574  // else
5575  // if rhs < -1 then
5576  // lhs / rhs
5577  // else if rhs == 0 then
5578  // 0
5579  // else
5580  // 0 - lhs
5581  //
5582  // Note: We do not use the Diamond helper class here, because it really hurts
5583  // readability with nested diamonds.
5584  const Operator* const merge_op = common()->Merge(2);
5585  const Operator* const phi_op =
5586  common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, 2);
5587 
5588  Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32LessThan(), zero, rhs);
5589  Node* branch0 = graph()->NewNode(
5590  common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check0,
5591  graph()->start());
5592 
5593  Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
5594  Node* true0 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Div(), lhs, rhs, if_true0);
5595 
5596  Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
5597  Node* false0;
5598  {
5599  Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32LessThan(), rhs, minus_one);
5600  Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(
5601  common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check1,
5602  if_false0);
5603 
5604  Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
5605  Node* true1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Div(), lhs, rhs, if_true1);
5606 
5607  Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
5608  Node* false1;
5609  {
5610  Node* check2 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32Equal(), rhs, zero);
5611  Node* branch2 = graph()->NewNode(
5612  common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone, BranchSemantics::kMachine),
5613  check2, if_false1);
5614 
5615  Node* if_true2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch2);
5616  Node* true2 = zero;
5617 
5618  Node* if_false2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch2);
5619  Node* false2 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Sub(), zero, lhs);
5620 
5621  if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true2, if_false2);
5622  false1 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true2, false2, if_false1);
5623  }
5624 
5625  if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true1, if_false1);
5626  false0 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true1, false1, if_false0);
5627  }
5628 
5629  Node* merge0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true0, if_false0);
5630  return graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true0, false0, merge0);
5631 }
5632 
5633 Node* SimplifiedLowering::Int32Mod(Node* const node) {
5634  Int32BinopMatcher m(node);
5635  Node* const zero = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0);
5636  Node* const minus_one = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(-1);
5637  Node* const lhs = m.left().node();
5638  Node* const rhs = m.right().node();
5639 
5640  if (m.right().Is(-1) || m.right().Is(0)) {
5641  return zero;
5642  } else if (m.right().HasResolvedValue()) {
5643  return graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Mod(), lhs, rhs, graph()->start());
5644  }
5645 
5646  // General case for signed integer modulus, with optimization for (unknown)
5647  // power of 2 right hand side.
5648  //
5649  // if 0 < rhs then
5650  // msk = rhs - 1
5651  // if rhs & msk != 0 then
5652  // lhs % rhs
5653  // else
5654  // if lhs < 0 then
5655  // -(-lhs & msk)
5656  // else
5657  // lhs & msk
5658  // else
5659  // if rhs < -1 then
5660  // lhs % rhs
5661  // else
5662  // zero
5663  //
5664  // Note: We do not use the Diamond helper class here, because it really hurts
5665  // readability with nested diamonds.
5666  const Operator* const merge_op = common()->Merge(2);
5667  const Operator* const phi_op =
5668  common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, 2);
5669 
5670  Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32LessThan(), zero, rhs);
5671  Node* branch0 = graph()->NewNode(
5672  common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check0,
5673  graph()->start());
5674 
5675  Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
5676  Node* true0;
5677  {
5678  Node* msk = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Add(), rhs, minus_one);
5679 
5680  Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32And(), rhs, msk);
5681  Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(
5682  common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check1,
5683  if_true0);
5684 
5685  Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
5686  Node* true1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Mod(), lhs, rhs, if_true1);
5687 
5688  Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
5689  Node* false1;
5690  {
5691  Node* check2 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32LessThan(), lhs, zero);
5692  Node* branch2 = graph()->NewNode(
5693  common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse, BranchSemantics::kMachine),
5694  check2, if_false1);
5695 
5696  Node* if_true2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch2);
5697  Node* true2 = graph()->NewNode(
5698  machine()->Int32Sub(), zero,
5699  graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32And(),
5700  graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Sub(), zero, lhs),
5701  msk));
5702 
5703  Node* if_false2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch2);
5704  Node* false2 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32And(), lhs, msk);
5705 
5706  if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true2, if_false2);
5707  false1 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true2, false2, if_false1);
5708  }
5709 
5710  if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true1, if_false1);
5711  true0 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true1, false1, if_true0);
5712  }
5713 
5714  Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
5715  Node* false0;
5716  {
5717  Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32LessThan(), rhs, minus_one);
5718  Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(
5719  common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check1,
5720  if_false0);
5721 
5722  Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
5723  Node* true1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Mod(), lhs, rhs, if_true1);
5724 
5725  Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
5726  Node* false1 = zero;
5727 
5728  if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true1, if_false1);
5729  false0 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true1, false1, if_false0);
5730  }
5731 
5732  Node* merge0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true0, if_false0);
5733  return graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true0, false0, merge0);
5734 }

5736 Node* SimplifiedLowering::Int32Sign(Node* const node) {
5737  Node* const minus_one = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(-1);
5738  Node* const zero = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0);
5739  Node* const one = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(1);
5740 
5741  Node* const input = node->InputAt(0);
5742 
5743  return graph()->NewNode(
5744  common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kWord32),
5745  graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32LessThan(), input, zero), minus_one,
5746  graph()->NewNode(
5747  common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kWord32),
5748  graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32LessThan(), zero, input), one,
5749  zero));
5750 }

5752 Node* SimplifiedLowering::Uint32Div(Node* const node) {
5753  Uint32BinopMatcher m(node);
5754  Node* const zero = jsgraph()->Uint32Constant(0);
5755  Node* const lhs = m.left().node();
5756  Node* const rhs = m.right().node();
5757 
5758  if (m.right().Is(0)) {
5759  return zero;
5760  } else if (machine()->Uint32DivIsSafe() || m.right().HasResolvedValue()) {
5761  return graph()->NewNode(machine()->Uint32Div(), lhs, rhs, graph()->start());
5762  }
5763 
5764  Node* check = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32Equal(), rhs, zero);
5765  Diamond d(graph(), common(), check, BranchHint::kFalse,
5766  BranchSemantics::kMachine);
5767  Node* div = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Uint32Div(), lhs, rhs, d.if_false);
5768  return d.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, zero, div);
5769 }

5771 Node* SimplifiedLowering::Uint32Mod(Node* const node) {
5772  Uint32BinopMatcher m(node);
5773  Node* const minus_one = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(-1);
5774  Node* const zero = jsgraph()->Uint32Constant(0);
5775  Node* const lhs = m.left().node();
5776  Node* const rhs = m.right().node();
5777 
5778  if (m.right().Is(0)) {
5779  return zero;
5780  } else if (m.right().HasResolvedValue()) {
5781  return graph()->NewNode(machine()->Uint32Mod(), lhs, rhs, graph()->start());
5782  }
5783 
5784  // General case for unsigned integer modulus, with optimization for (unknown)
5785  // power of 2 right hand side.
5786  //
5787  // if rhs == 0 then
5788  // zero
5789  // else
5790  // msk = rhs - 1
5791  // if rhs & msk != 0 then
5792  // lhs % rhs
5793  // else
5794  // lhs & msk
5795  //
5796  // Note: We do not use the Diamond helper class here, because it really hurts
5797  // readability with nested diamonds.
5798  const Operator* const merge_op = common()->Merge(2);
5799  const Operator* const phi_op =
5800  common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, 2);
5801 
5802  Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32Equal(), rhs, zero);
5803  Node* branch0 = graph()->NewNode(
5804  common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check0,
5805  graph()->start());
5806 
5807  Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
5808  Node* true0 = zero;
5809 
5810  Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
5811  Node* false0;
5812  {
5813  Node* msk = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Add(), rhs, minus_one);
5814 
5815  Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32And(), rhs, msk);
5816  Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(
5817  common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check1,
5818  if_false0);
5819 
5820  Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
5821  Node* true1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Uint32Mod(), lhs, rhs, if_true1);
5822 
5823  Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
5824  Node* false1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32And(), lhs, msk);
5825 
5826  if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true1, if_false1);
5827  false0 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true1, false1, if_false0);
5828  }
5829 
5830  Node* merge0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true0, if_false0);
5831  return graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true0, false0, merge0);
5832 }

5834 void SimplifiedLowering::DoMax(Node* node, Operator const* op,
5835  MachineRepresentation rep) {
5836  Node* const lhs = node->InputAt(0);
5837  Node* const rhs = node->InputAt(1);
5838 
5839  node->ReplaceInput(0, graph()->NewNode(op, lhs, rhs));
5840  DCHECK_EQ(rhs, node->InputAt(1));
5841  node->AppendInput(graph()->zone(), lhs);
5842  ChangeOp(node, common()->Select(rep));
5843 }
5844 
5845 void SimplifiedLowering::DoMin(Node* node, Operator const* op,
5846  MachineRepresentation rep) {
5847  Node* const lhs = node->InputAt(0);
5848  Node* const rhs = node->InputAt(1);
5849 
5850  node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 0, graph()->NewNode(op, lhs, rhs));
5851  DCHECK_EQ(lhs, node->InputAt(1));
5852  DCHECK_EQ(rhs, node->InputAt(2));
5853  ChangeOp(node, common()->Select(rep));
5854 }
